I WANNA GO HOME.
OH, IT'S GONNA BE FINE, MAN.

07:21.667 --> 07:23.041
IT'S GONNA BE
BETTER THAN FINE.

07:23.125 --> 07:25.709
I MEAN, LOOK AT ALL THIS
NEW AND INTERESTING--

07:25.792 --> 07:27.750
HEY, THAT'S MY SISTER!

07:27.834 --> 07:29.417
♪ YOU GOT TO BE INSANE ♪

07:29.500 --> 07:31.750
HEY, GRABBY HANDS,
STEP AWAY FROM THE SISTER.

07:31.834 --> 07:33.625
♪ YOU GOT TO BE INSANE ♪

07:33.709 --> 07:36.583
SHOULDN'T YOU BE AT, LIKE, A
PAJAMA JAMMY-JAM OR SOMETHIN'?

07:36.667 --> 07:38.625
WHAT AM I,
A YEAR YOUNGER THAN YOU?

07:38.709 --> 07:43.667
NOT THAN ANYBODY COULD TELL
FROM YOUR BIRTHDAY PRESENTS--
PINK ROLLERBLADES.

07:43.750 --> 07:45.792
IT WAS A GREAT GIFT.
SURE.

07:45.875 --> 07:47.959
CAN I HELP YOU?
HUH?

07:48.041 --> 07:50.458
UH... NO.
COME ON, BASIN.

07:50.542 --> 07:53.000
THERE'S A GUY IN THE CORNER WHO
SAYS HE'LL PIERCE OUR NAVELS FOR
FREE.

07:53.083 --> 07:55.417
OOH!
WHAT?

07:55.500 --> 07:58.583
OK, HE'S HERE. HE'S HERE.
SO?

07:58.667 --> 08:00.917
SO I TOLD HIM I WAS GOING
OUT OF TOWN, MAGGIE.

08:01.000 --> 08:03.458
HE'S GONNA FREAK
WHEN HE FINDS OUT I'M HERE.

08:03.542 --> 08:05.625
AL, YOU'RE A FREE AGENT NOW.

08:05.709 --> 08:07.583
DON'T YOU THINK HE NEEDS
TO START DEALING WITH THAT?

08:07.667 --> 08:11.667
YOU SHOULD'VE SEEN THE LOOK
ON HIS FACE, MAGGIE. I MEAN,
HE WAS DEVASTATED.

08:11.750 --> 08:14.500
IT'S GONNA TAKE HIM A WHILE
TO GET OVER THIS.
ALLISON?

08:14.583 --> 08:16.667
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE OVER THIS?

08:19.417 --> 08:20.458
ALLOW ME.

08:20.542 --> 08:22.125
♪ SAY YEAH
WHAT DO YOU WANT? ♪

08:22.208 --> 08:25.083
♪ [ Continues ]

08:26.750 --> 08:29.917
WHO WAS THAT? OUCH!

08:31.917 --> 08:33.875
IS THIS, LIKE, YOUR FIRST TIME
IN THE STATES?

08:33.958 --> 08:36.667
WELL, UH--
LUCKY, RIGHT?

08:36.750 --> 08:38.332
[ Giggling ]

08:38.417 --> 08:40.625
ARE YOU GUYS LISTENING
TO THIS CANDY-ASS?

08:40.708 --> 08:44.709
MY FATHER'S IN THE FOREIGN
SERVICE, SO I'VE SPENT
THE LAST FEW YEARS ABROAD--

08:44.792 --> 08:47.500
SHANGHAI, LUDWIGSHAFEN.

08:47.583 --> 08:48.542
IN FACT,
WHEN I WAS IN AMSTERDAM,

08:48.625 --> 08:50.667
I TOURED A LITTLE BIT
WITH A LITTLE POP GROUP

08:50.750 --> 08:52.709
CALLED THE SWING TOWN LADS.

08:52.792 --> 08:54.125
[ Girls gasping, Chattering ]

08:54.208 --> 08:56.125
YOU KNOW,
I KNEW HE LOOKED FAMILIAR.

08:56.208 --> 08:59.125
WHAT'S UP WITH THIS ACCENT?
HE SOUNDS LIKE MADONNA.

09:01.583 --> 09:03.417
SHE'S HERE.
WHO, MADONNA?

09:04.792 --> 09:07.375
NO. ALLISON.

09:07.458 --> 09:09.917
OHH!
IT'S PERFECT.

09:10.000 --> 09:13.709
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
YOU ARE NOT GOING OVER THERE.

09:13.792 --> 09:17.709
YOU GO OVER THERE,
YOU MIGHT AS WELL
PUT YOUR STICK ON A CRACKER.

09:17.792 --> 09:21.959
YOU KNOW, IT'S STILL ONLY GONNA
MAKE YOU HER BITCH.
YOU DON'T WANT THAT. IT'S BAD!

09:22.834 --> 09:24.709
FELIX, I'VE TAKEN PISSES

09:24.792 --> 09:27.000
LONGER THAN YOUR
LAST THREE RELATIONSHIPS.

09:27.792 --> 09:30.500
OHH!
OH! RIGHT YOU ARE.

09:30.583 --> 09:32.208
THANKS.
YOU OK?

09:32.291 --> 09:33.709
YES. YEAH. I THINK SO.

09:33.792 --> 09:35.875
YES, WELL, IT'S A TAD
ROUGH-AND-TUMBLE OUT THERE.

09:35.959 --> 09:37.709
GLAD I WAS HERE TO CATCH YOU.

09:37.792 --> 09:40.166
I'M GLAD YOU WERE, TOO.

09:40.250 --> 09:41.375
[ Gasps ]

09:41.458 --> 09:43.750
WOULD YOU CARE TO DANCE?

09:43.834 --> 09:46.834
♪ [ Salsa ]

10:15.834 --> 10:19.041
♪ [ Continues ]

10:47.917 --> 10:50.000
SHE'S NOT YOUR GIRLFRIEND
ANYMORE, MAN.

10:50.083 --> 10:52.500
YOU KNOW, MAYBE THAT'S NOT
SUCH A BAD THING.

10:52.583 --> 10:55.458
I MEAN, NEXT YEAR
YOU GUYS'LL BE GOING
TO DIFFERENT SCHOOLS.

10:55.542 --> 10:57.458
I MEAN, WHAT WERE YOU GONNA DO,
MARRY HER?

10:57.542 --> 10:59.792
I MEAN, COME ON, WHO MARRIES
THEIR HIGH-SCHOOL GIRLFRIEND,
ANYWAY?

10:59.875 --> 11:01.625
AND DON'T SAY MACAULAY CULKIN.

11:01.709 --> 11:03.792
[ Phone Beeping ]
I THINK I'M GONNA CALL HER.

11:03.875 --> 11:06.000
NO. NEGATIVE.

11:06.083 --> 11:08.458
[ Groans ]
HAVE SOME SELF-RESPECT, MAN.

11:08.542 --> 11:10.917
YOU HAVE CALLED HER 40 TIMES
ALREADY.

11:13.291 --> 11:15.291
GET OUTTA MY WAY!
OH, SHIT.

11:16.291 --> 11:19.000
♪ I, I STAND AT ATTENTION ♪

11:19.083 --> 11:21.834
♪ WHENEVER YOU'RE NEAR ♪
♪ YOU'RE NEAR ♪

11:21.917 --> 11:25.709
♪ FULL SPEED AHEAD GIRL
'CAUSE IT'S CLEAR ♪

11:25.792 --> 11:30.166
♪ THAT YOU ARE MY LUV S.C.U.D. ♪

11:30.250 --> 11:32.375
[ Maggie ]
HE CALLS HIMSELF STRIKER.

11:32.458 --> 11:36.875
[ Allison Giggling ]
"LUV S.C.U.D.?"

11:36.959 --> 11:39.208
SO WHAT DID HE SAY
WHEN HE GAVE IT TO YOU?

11:39.291 --> 11:42.875
MM, I DON'T KNOW.
HE ASKED ME OUT.

11:42.959 --> 11:47.291
[ Gasps ]
WELL, DON'T BE SO NONCHALANT
ABOUT IT, GIRL.

11:47.375 --> 11:50.542
I THINK THAT BOY IS RAZOR FINE.

11:50.625 --> 11:52.834
[ Berke ]
♪ OH, IT'S SO FUNNY
TO BE SEEIN' YOU ♪

11:52.917 --> 11:54.083
[ Felix ]
LOOK, BERKE, DON'T GO--

11:54.166 --> 11:55.750
♪ AFTER SO LONG, GIRL ♪
OH, MY GOD.

11:55.834 --> 11:58.750
BERKE, DON'T-- DON'T--
♪ AND THE WAY YOU LOOK
I UNDERSTAND ♪

11:58.834 --> 12:02.208
♪ THAT YOU AREN'T IMPRESSED ♪

12:02.291 --> 12:06.333
♪ I HEARD YOU LET
A LITTLE FRIEND OF MINE ♪

12:06.417 --> 12:09.875
♪ TAKE OFF YOUR PARTY DRESS ♪

12:09.959 --> 12:13.917
♪ OH, ALLISON ♪

12:14.000 --> 12:16.750
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU DATED
THAT LOSER FOR A YEAR.
♪ I KNOW THIS WORLD ♪

12:16.834 --> 12:18.875
♪ IS KILLIN' YOU ♪
[ Woman ]
KNOCK IT OFF!
WE'LL CALL THE COPS!

12:18.959 --> 12:20.875
♪ ALLISON ♪
[ Felix ]
DID YOU HEAR THAT?

12:20.959 --> 12:22.750
THE NEIGHBORS
ARE SCREAMING AT YOU, BERKE!

12:22.834 --> 12:24.667
♪ MY AIM IS-- ♪
COME ON, LET'S GO!

12:24.750 --> 12:26.542
[ Crash, Thud ]

12:26.625 --> 12:29.542
[ Berke Screams, Whines ]

12:29.625 --> 12:31.208
BERKE, YOUR AIM SUCKS.

12:34.208 --> 12:37.917
ALL RIGHT, A LITTLE TO THE LEFT,
JESSICA-- WHAT DIRECTION
DO YOU THINK LEFT IS?

12:38.000 --> 12:39.959
SEE, BECAUSE IF YOU GO WITH
YOUR INSTINCT AND REVERSE IT

12:40.041 --> 12:41.250
I THINK WE HAVE
SOMETHING HAPPENING.

12:41.333 --> 12:45.542
HOW DIFFICULT IS THIS?
I-- I'M SO ALONE, I THINK.

12:45.625 --> 12:47.542
I AM TRYING.
YOU ARE INTIMIDATING ME.

12:47.625 --> 12:50.375
WELL, YOU ARE FRIGHTENING ME!
DO YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?

12:50.458 --> 12:51.625
HOW DO YOU GET DRESSED
IN THE MORNING?

12:51.709 --> 12:53.083
DO YOU HAVE PEOPLE THAT COME IN

12:53.166 --> 12:54.959
OR YOU JUST LIE IN STATE?

12:55.041 --> 12:57.917
"A MIDSUMMER NIGHT'S
ROCKIN' EVE?"

12:58.000 --> 13:01.625
CLASSICAL SHAKESPEARE WITH
A CONTEMPORARY MUSICAL TWIST.
[ Phone Rings ]

13:01.709 --> 13:06.083
HELLO? OH, MY GOD!
HOW DID YOU GET THIS NUMBER?

13:06.166 --> 13:07.375
[ Laughs ]
OH, YOU'RE KIDDING ME!

13:07.458 --> 13:09.750
OK, EITHER THAT MAN
HAS NO TASTE

13:09.834 --> 13:10.875
OR HE COMPLETELY HATES US.

13:10.959 --> 13:12.917
I THINK IT'S A LITTLE OF BOTH.

13:13.041 --> 13:15.417
LAZARIO, HOW'S THAT LOBOTOMY
WORKIN' OUT FOR YA?

13:15.500 --> 13:17.458
ASI, ASI.
SO WHAT'S WITH THE SMILING?

13:17.542 --> 13:20.125
A WEEK AGO YOU WERE MIRED
IN REJECTED DRUNK-GUY MODE.

13:20.208 --> 13:23.458
YOU PASS THE FINAL OR WHAT?
NO, I GOT A 57.

13:23.542 --> 13:26.917
OUCH.
[ Striker ]
HELLO, LADIES.

13:27.000 --> 13:29.959
[ Felix ]
I'M SORRY, MAN.
I MEAN, THAT'S THAT'S GOTTA
SUCK.

13:30.041 --> 13:33.417
NO, JUST A MILD ANNOYANCE.
SEE? YEAH! THERE YOU GO.

13:33.500 --> 13:35.750
ALL RIGHT, YOU KNOW,
IF SHE WANTS TO SCREW AROUND

13:35.834 --> 13:36.834
WITH THAT CLOWN, LET HER, RIGHT?

13:36.917 --> 13:40.125
YEAH, FOR NOW, ANYWAY.
WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

13:40.208 --> 13:44.625
WELL, IF I'M GONNA LOSE ALLISON,
IT'S NOT GOING TO BE
TO A TURD LIKE THAT, RIGHT?

13:44.709 --> 13:46.667
[ Male Singer ]
♪ I'M NOT UPSET ♪

13:46.750 --> 13:48.208
[ Whistle Blows ]

13:48.291 --> 13:50.667
YOU KNOW, OBVIOUSLY, THERE'S
SOMETHING ABOUT THE GUY
ALLISON REALLY LIKES.

13:50.750 --> 13:51.667
YEAH, OBVIOUSLY.

13:51.750 --> 13:52.792
♪ [ Continues ]

13:52.875 --> 13:54.750
COME ON, LANDERS,
WAKE UP OUT THERE!

13:56.291 --> 13:58.375
[ Coach ]
FANCY MOVES, CRAZY LEGS.

14:00.625 --> 14:03.208
IN YOUR FACE.
GOD, THERE HE IS AGAIN.

14:03.291 --> 14:06.500
I DON'T KNOW HOW YOU COULD
TAKE SOMEONE SERIOUSLY
WITH AN ACCENT LIKE THAT.

14:06.583 --> 14:08.458
BERKE, JUST FACE IT, MAN.
YOU'RE SCREWED.

14:08.542 --> 14:11.834
I DON'T THINK SO. I THINK I CAN
TAKE THIS BACKSTREET BITCH.

14:11.917 --> 14:14.667
[ Chuckles ]
[ Whistle Blows ]

14:19.208 --> 14:20.667
[ Girl ]
OHH!

14:20.750 --> 14:22.417
[ Boy Laughs ]

14:23.917 --> 14:26.834
NICE TRICK, LANDERS, CATCHING
THE BALL WITH YOUR FACE.

14:26.917 --> 14:31.000
NEXT THING YOU KNOW,
YOU'LL BE SHOOTING
THREE-POINTERS WITH YOUR ASS.

14:31.083 --> 14:33.667
[ Sighs ]
BERKE.

14:33.750 --> 14:35.000
BERKE, STOP. BERKE!

14:35.083 --> 14:39.041
WILL YOU LET ME LOOK AT IT,
PLEASE?
JUST GO BACK TO PRACTICE.

14:39.125 --> 14:41.417
BERKE, TALK TO ME.

14:42.959 --> 14:47.917
I JUST DON'T UNDERSTAND
HOW YOU CAN REPLACE ME
WITH THIS GUY.

14:48.000 --> 14:53.041
BERKE, NO ONE CAN REPLACE YOU,
YOU KNOW?

14:53.125 --> 14:55.792
IT'S JUST... TIME TO MOVE ON.

14:57.500 --> 15:01.333
SO EVERYTHING'S JUST GOING GREAT
WITH THIS, THIS STRIKER?

15:02.917 --> 15:04.875
NO, IT-- IT'S JUST...

15:04.959 --> 15:08.208
UH, DIFFERENT, YOU KNOW?
I MEAN--

15:08.291 --> 15:11.041
HE'S NOT LIKE OTHER GUYS
OUR AGE. YOU KNOW?

15:11.125 --> 15:13.500
HE'S-- HE'S SOPHISTICATED AND--

15:13.583 --> 15:19.917
WE'RE EVEN GONNA TRY OUT
FOR-- FOR THE-- THE SPRING
MUSICAL TOGETHER.

15:20.000 --> 15:21.625
YOU HATE THEATER.

15:23.542 --> 15:24.834
NO, I DON'T.

15:27.291 --> 15:29.750
"CAPTAIN OF THE FAIRY BAND,

15:29.834 --> 15:33.083
HELENA IS CLOSE AT HAND."

15:33.166 --> 15:35.917
I'M UNDERSTANDING ABOUT EVERY
OTHER WORD OF THIS SHIT.

15:36.000 --> 15:38.250
BERKE.
HEY.

15:38.333 --> 15:42.083
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR FACE?
A LONG STORY.

15:42.166 --> 15:46.542
A MIDSUMMER NIGHT'S DREAM?
WHAT, ARE YOU GONNA TRY OUT
FOR THE SHOW?

15:46.625 --> 15:48.041
KINDA, SOR-- MAYBE.

15:48.125 --> 15:53.125
WELL, YOU KNOW,
IF YOU'RE SERIOUS ABOUT IT,
I'M KINDA GOOD AT THAT STUFF.

15:53.208 --> 15:55.750
REALLY?
HAVE YOU HEARD HER SONGS?

15:55.834 --> 15:59.583
SHE'S ONLY LIKE
THE NEXT JOSIE MITCHELL.
JONI MITCHELL.

15:59.667 --> 16:02.291
I-- I COULD ACTUALLY
USE SOME HELP.

16:02.375 --> 16:05.208
SO TOMORROW, COFFEE?

16:06.166 --> 16:09.625
OK. COFFEE WOULD BE GREAT.
OK.

16:09.709 --> 16:11.792
BYE.
BYE.

16:11.875 --> 16:13.417
[ Giggling ]

16:13.500 --> 16:16.083
"IF YOU'RE SERIOUS,
I'M KINDA GOOD AT THAT STUFF."

16:16.166 --> 16:17.583
SHUT UP!
"SHUT UP!"
[ Gasps ]

16:17.667 --> 16:19.792
DID YOU SEE DENNIS
STARING AT ME AGAIN?
WHAT? OH, I KNOW.

16:19.875 --> 16:21.125
I TOLD YOU.
TOTALLY.

16:21.208 --> 16:22.917
OK, SO THE FIRST THING
WE NEED TO DO

16:23.000 --> 16:26.166
IS PICK YOU OUT A MONOLOGUE
FOR YOUR AUDITION.

16:26.250 --> 16:28.208
YEAH, THIS IS GOOD.
LYSANDER, RIGHT?

16:31.709 --> 16:34.000
[ Rapidly ]
UH, "SHE SEES NOT HERMIA.
HERMIA SLEEP THOU THERE--"

16:34.083 --> 16:38.458
NO, WAIT, NO. YOU-- YOU CAN'T,
LIKE, RUN ALL THE WORDS
TOGETHER. IT DOESN'T WORK
LIKE THAT.

16:38.542 --> 16:41.333
BUT THAT'S OK. WE'LL-- WE'LL
START FROM THE BEGINNING, OK?

16:41.417 --> 16:43.166
IT'S-- IT'S KIND OF HARD
TO UNDERSTAND,

16:43.250 --> 16:46.959
BUT ONCE YOU GET INTO IT,
THE STORY'S ACTUALLY
KIND OF GOOD.

16:47.041 --> 16:52.166
SO, HERMIA, THIS GIRL HERE,
SHE'S VERY RICH AND BEAUTIFUL

16:52.250 --> 16:55.333
AND SHE LIVES WITH
HER OVERBEARING PARENTS
IN ATHENS.

16:55.417 --> 16:58.041
NOW, HERMIA HAS EVERYTHING
A GIRL COULD ASK FOR,

16:58.125 --> 17:03.333
COOL CLOTHES, NICE COMPLEXION
AND HER PICK OF PRETTY MUCH
ANY GUY SHE WANTS.

17:03.417 --> 17:06.000
BUT OF ALL THE GUYS
IN THE GREATER ATHENS AREA,

17:06.083 --> 17:09.165
HERMIA'S HEART BELONGS
TO THE HANDSOME YOUNG NOBLEMAN,
LYSANDER.

17:09.250 --> 17:10.834
[ Horse Whinnies ]

17:10.916 --> 17:14.625
THIS WOULD ALL BE PERFECT
IF IT WEREN'T FOR DEMETRIUS.

17:14.709 --> 17:17.165
HERMIA'S FATHER ALREADY
PROMISED HER HAND TO HIM,

17:17.250 --> 17:22.125
AND HE'S JUST AS CHARMING
AND HANDSOME AS LYSANDER,
MAYBE EVEN MORE SO.

17:22.208 --> 17:26.500
NOT TO MENTION,
DEMETRIUS WILL STOP AT NOTHING
TO MAKE HERMIA HIS BRIDE.

17:26.583 --> 17:29.125
THIS PRETTY MUCH
LEAVES LYSANDER SCREWED.

17:31.291 --> 17:33.208
ALL RIGHT. GOT IT.

17:33.291 --> 17:37.834
UH, YOU MAKE IT, UH, VERY EASY.

17:37.917 --> 17:39.375
WE JUST STARTED.

17:39.458 --> 17:42.041
KELLY, I'M NOT EXACTLY
TRYING TO WIN AN OSCAR HERE.

17:42.125 --> 17:46.417
I'M JUST TRYING TO GET
MY GIRLFRIEND BACK. THANKS.

17:49.750 --> 17:51.667
HI! HOW ARE YOU?

17:51.750 --> 17:54.542
HI, NEW FACES,
HOW ARE YOU TODAY?

17:54.625 --> 17:56.333
I'M DR. DESMOND FORREST OATES,

17:56.417 --> 18:00.208
FINE ARTS CHAIR
AND ALL THAT HOOPLA.

18:00.291 --> 18:01.875
THE PURPOSE
OF THESE PROCEEDINGS

18:01.959 --> 18:05.083
IS TO SEPARATE
THE WHEAT FROM THE CHAFF.

18:05.166 --> 18:10.291
AND I THINK WE MIGHT BE AMAZED
THAT AMONG US
IS A NEW GLIMMERING STAR,

18:10.375 --> 18:13.083
OUR SCHOOL'S NEXT--

18:13.166 --> 18:16.041
WELL, OUR NEXT PETER WONG.

18:16.125 --> 18:18.917
[ Kids Chattering, Scoffing ]
HEY, PETEY.

18:19.000 --> 18:20.166
COOL SHIRT.

18:21.792 --> 18:23.750
FOR THOSE OF YOU
WHO DON'T MAKE THE CUT,

18:23.834 --> 18:25.458
PLEASE, I BEG OF YOU,
DON'T DESPAIR.

18:25.542 --> 18:27.000
THERE'S ALWAYS STAGE CREW.

18:27.083 --> 18:29.583
AND IF YOU'VE EVER
HAD A CONVERSATION
WITH A CREW MEMBER,

18:29.667 --> 18:31.709
YOU KNOW HOW MUCH FUN
THAT CAN BE.
[ Farting ]

18:31.792 --> 18:34.291
I'M KIDDING, I'M KIDDING.
I COULDN'T RESIST IT.

18:34.375 --> 18:36.542
YOU EGG ME ON, IS THE PROBLEM.

18:36.625 --> 18:39.375
ALL RIGHT, THE PROCEDURE IS
GONNA BE VERY, VERY, VERY BASIC.

18:39.458 --> 18:41.291
WE'RE GONNA START
WITH THE SINGING AUDITION.

18:41.375 --> 18:45.208
OK? SO LOOSEN UP
THOSE DIAPHRAGMS, KIDDIES.

18:45.291 --> 18:47.291
IT'S TIME TO IMPRESS.

18:47.375 --> 18:51.291
[ Falsetto, Soprano ]
♪ WHERE THE BEE SUCKS
THERE SUCK I ♪

18:51.375 --> 18:53.959
♪ IN A COWSLIP'S BELL I LIE ♪

18:54.041 --> 18:56.959
♪ THERE I COUCH
WHEN OWLS DO CRY ♪

18:57.041 --> 18:59.667
[ Basso ]
♪ ON THE BAT'S BACK I DO FLY ♪

18:59.750 --> 19:05.291
[ Falsetto, Soprano ]
♪ AFTER SUMMER MERRILY-Y-Y-Y-Y ♪

19:05.375 --> 19:08.500
♪ TAKE A LOOK
HERE I AM ♪

19:08.583 --> 19:11.750
♪ CAN'T YOU SEE? ♪

19:11.834 --> 19:16.291
♪ ONE SIMPLE SMILE FROM YOU
COULD SET ME FREE ♪

19:16.375 --> 19:19.750
♪ SO IF YOU TAKE A LOOK ♪

19:19.834 --> 19:24.250
♪ LET YOUR HEART BE YOUR GUIDE ♪

19:24.333 --> 19:26.125
♪ I'LL SHOW YOU LOVE ♪

19:26.208 --> 19:28.208
♪ IF YOU TAKE A LOOK ♪

19:28.291 --> 19:33.667
♪ AT THE GIRL INSIDE ♪

19:33.750 --> 19:38.208
OH, THAT WAS-- THAT WAS FUN.
WHO'S THE COMPOSER ON THAT?

19:38.291 --> 19:40.875
ME, ACTUALLY.

19:40.959 --> 19:44.667
I'M SORRY, WERE YOU--
WERE YOU EXPECTING AN APPLAUSE
ON THAT?

19:44.750 --> 19:46.500
THIS IS AN AUDITION, NOT T.R.L.

19:46.583 --> 19:49.542
[ Forrest Oates Chuckles ]
I KNOW THAT.

19:49.625 --> 19:52.834
WHO'S NEXT? "BENTLEY SCRUMFELD."

19:52.917 --> 19:55.834
ONE OF THE ORIGINAL
SWING TOWN LADS,
IF I'M NOT MISTAKEN.

19:55.917 --> 19:58.000
I SEE YOU KNOW YOUR BOY GROUPS,
SIR.

19:58.083 --> 20:00.125
I FOLLOW THE POPULAR ARTS.

20:01.417 --> 20:03.458
TO ME THEY'RE SO DOPE.

20:03.542 --> 20:07.834
IF YOU DON'T MIND,
I'D LIKE TO ACCOMPANY MYSELF.

20:07.917 --> 20:09.625
AH. PUT THAT DOWN.

20:10.458 --> 20:12.417
THANK YOU.

20:12.500 --> 20:16.417
THIS ONE'S KIND OF
A PERSONAL FAVORITE OF MINE.

20:16.500 --> 20:19.500
♪ [ Piano: Glissando ]

20:19.583 --> 20:21.583
[ Girls Giggling, Sighing ]

20:21.667 --> 20:23.667
♪ OH, IT'S SO FUNNY ♪

20:23.750 --> 20:28.208
♪ TO BE SEEING YOU
AFTER SO LONG, GIRL ♪

20:28.291 --> 20:31.333
♪ AND THE WAY YOU LOOK
I UNDERSTAND ♪

20:31.417 --> 20:34.500
♪ THAT YOU ARE NOT IMPRESSED ♪

20:34.583 --> 20:40.375
♪ BUT I HEARD YOU LET
THAT LITTLE FRIEND OF MINE ♪

20:40.458 --> 20:43.583
♪ TAKE OFF YOUR PARTY DRESS ♪

20:43.667 --> 20:45.375
[ Gasps, Whispers ]
OH, MY.

20:45.458 --> 20:50.583
♪ ALLISON ♪

20:50.667 --> 20:57.208
♪ I KNOW THIS WORLD
IS KILLIN' YOU ♪

20:57.291 --> 21:01.875
♪ ALLISON ♪

21:01.959 --> 21:03.583
[ Girls Murmuring, Chattering ]

21:03.667 --> 21:05.458
♪ MY AIM IS TRUE ♪
HE'S THE BEST ONE.

21:05.542 --> 21:07.500
HE'S THE BEST ONE
WE'VE SEEN SO FAR.

21:09.542 --> 21:12.750
♪ MY AIM IS ♪

21:12.834 --> 21:14.417
[ Guttural Whisper ]
TRUE.

21:14.500 --> 21:17.750
♪ [ Chords: Glissando ]

21:17.834 --> 21:19.041
[ Girls Murmuring, Chattering ]

21:19.125 --> 21:20.041
♪ [ End Chords ]

21:20.125 --> 21:21.333
VERY NICE, MR. STRIKER.

21:21.417 --> 21:24.250
[ Girls Cheering, Shouting ]
THAT IS VERY IMPRESSIVE INDEED.

21:24.333 --> 21:27.417
THAT'S, UH, THAT'S-- WOW.

21:27.500 --> 21:29.083
ALRIGHTY. WELL,
IF THERE'S NO ONE ELSE--

21:29.166 --> 21:30.959
WAIT.
[ Girl ]
WHAT?

21:31.041 --> 21:34.959
MAY I HELP YOU?
BERKE LANDERS.
I'M HERE TO AUDITION.

21:35.041 --> 21:39.667
[ Forrest Oates ]
AH. BERKE LANDERS. GOODY FOR ME.

21:39.750 --> 21:44.333
UH, I'D LIKE TO READ A MONOLOGUE
BY OBERON IN THE THIRD ACT.

21:44.417 --> 21:48.750
OH, I CAN'T WAIT TO HEAR IT,
BUT FIRST I NEED TO HEAR
YOUR SINGING AUDITION.

21:48.834 --> 21:49.417
EXCUSE ME?

21:49.500 --> 21:50.917
THE PROCEDURE, MR. LANDERS,

21:51.000 --> 21:54.083
IS THAT WE SING FIRST
AND THEN WE READ LATER.

21:55.583 --> 21:57.500
UH--
[ Chuckles ]

21:57.583 --> 21:58.583
JESSICA, COULD YOU HELP ME HERE?

21:58.667 --> 22:01.458
I-I-I-I-I'M SINKING
IN QUICKSAND, UNFORTUNATELY,

22:01.542 --> 22:02.959
WITH THIS BOY.

22:03.041 --> 22:05.500
SING FIRST, READ LATER.
SING FIRST, READ LATER.

22:19.583 --> 22:23.041
ANY SONG?
ANY SONG YOU WANT.

22:25.417 --> 22:29.333
[ Whispering ]
♪ KISS A LITTLE LONGER
MAKE IT LAST A LITTLE LONGER ♪

22:29.417 --> 22:33.583
PROJECTION, MR. BERKE,
PROJECTION.

22:37.250 --> 22:38.959
♪ KISS A LITTLE LONGER ♪

22:39.041 --> 22:41.333
♪ STAY CLOSE A LITTLE LONGER ♪

22:41.417 --> 22:43.250
[ Students Groaning ]

22:48.583 --> 22:50.959
♪ HOLD TIGHT A LITTLE LONGER ♪

22:52.792 --> 22:55.417
♪ LONGER WITH BIG RED ♪

22:57.625 --> 23:02.166
♪ THAT BIG RED FRESHNESS
LASTS RIGHT THROUGH IT ♪

23:02.250 --> 23:04.500
[ Girls ]
♪ YOUR FRESH BREATH
GOES ON AND ON ♪

23:04.583 --> 23:06.166
[ Berke, Girls ]
♪ WHILE YOU CHEW IT ♪

23:06.250 --> 23:09.000
♪ SO SAY GOODBYE
A LITTLE LONGER ♪

23:09.083 --> 23:11.375
♪ MAKE IT LAST A LITTLE LONGER ♪

23:11.458 --> 23:15.542
♪ GIVE YOUR BREATH
LONG-LASTING FRESHNESS ♪

23:15.625 --> 23:17.583
♪ WITH BIG RED ♪

23:17.667 --> 23:20.625
[ Audience Applauding
And Cheering ]

23:24.000 --> 23:25.458
[ Phone Rings ]

23:27.000 --> 23:28.583
YEAH.
[ Berke ]
WHAT'S GOING ON?

23:28.667 --> 23:29.500
[ Dog Panting ]
OH, NOTHING.

23:29.583 --> 23:31.208
I'M JUST SITTING HERE
WATCHING CHESTER

23:31.291 --> 23:32.083
SCREW THE RUBBER TREE.

23:32.166 --> 23:34.083
WHAT IS THAT?
SOME KIND OF EXPRESSION?

23:34.166 --> 23:37.667
NO, NO, NO, NO.
MY AUNT'S DOG IS STAYING WITH US
FOR A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

23:37.750 --> 23:41.500
AND, APPARENTLY, HE'S GOT
SOME SORT OF HORMONAL IMBALANCE.

23:43.041 --> 23:45.583
WOW, UH--

23:45.667 --> 23:47.750
IS KELLY THERE?
WHAT?

23:47.834 --> 23:49.583
KELLY. YOUR SISTER.
IS SHE THERE?

23:49.667 --> 23:52.250
WHY?
'CAUSE SHE DID A FAVOR FOR ME
TODAY.

23:52.333 --> 23:56.208
JUST PUT HER ON, OK?
OK.

23:56.291 --> 23:57.333
HOLD, PLEASE.

24:00.125 --> 24:04.041
BERKE LANDERS.
SINCE WHEN DO MY FRIENDS
START CALLING YOU?

24:04.125 --> 24:06.417
SINCE TODAY. HEY.

24:06.500 --> 24:07.792
[ Berke ]
SO HOW WAS I?

24:09.125 --> 24:13.041
YOU WERE REALLY...
[ Sighs ] OK.

24:13.125 --> 24:14.792
SORRY. I THOUGHT YOU KNEW
ABOUT THE SINGING.

24:14.875 --> 24:18.458
OH, MINOR DETAIL.
YOU WERE CUTE.

24:18.542 --> 24:21.000
YOU WANNA TELL ALLISON THAT?

24:21.083 --> 24:23.583
WELL, I HOPE
YOU GET IN THE PLAY.

24:23.667 --> 24:26.625
WHAT?
FELIX?

24:26.709 --> 24:29.458
I CAN HEAR YOU BREATHING!

24:29.542 --> 24:31.834
HELLO?
[ Click, Dial Tone ]

24:33.709 --> 24:36.083
[ Jessica ]
ALL RIGHT, EVERYONE,
COMING THROUGH!

24:36.166 --> 24:38.667
OUT OF MY WAY! PART!

24:38.750 --> 24:41.250
PLEASE! EXCUSE ME. THANK YOU.

24:48.667 --> 24:50.166
OK, EV--
ALL RIGHT!

24:50.250 --> 24:53.083
[ Jessica ]
OW!
DEMETRIUS! YES!

24:53.166 --> 24:55.458
CONGRATULATIONS, FAIR HERMIA.
YOU'RE KIDDING.

24:55.542 --> 24:57.500
I KNEW YOU'D GET IT.
[ Screaming ]

24:57.583 --> 25:00.083
ALL RIGHT, PEOPLE,
THIS PLAY IS GONNA ROCK!

25:03.750 --> 25:07.667
CHORUS? OH, YOU'VE GOT TO BE
SHITTING ME.

25:07.750 --> 25:10.041
HELENA? OH, MY GOD!

25:10.125 --> 25:10.959
[ Squeals ]

25:11.041 --> 25:13.333
GOOD NEWS?
SORRY, I JUST--

25:13.417 --> 25:16.458
I REALLY HAD MY HEART SET
ON THAT PART.

25:16.542 --> 25:17.792
THAT'S-- THAT'S GOOD.

25:19.083 --> 25:23.041
LOOK, THERE'S YOU.
OH, YEAH.

25:23.125 --> 25:27.000
WELL, LET'S HOPE ATTENDANT #3
DOESN'T HAVE ANY SONGS.

25:27.083 --> 25:30.000
FELICITATIONS, MISS WOODS.
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

25:30.083 --> 25:32.709
IT'S A LEAD ROLE.
I KNOW.

25:32.792 --> 25:34.667
METHINKS
THOU BEST NOT BOTCH IT.

25:34.750 --> 25:35.917
[ Giggles ]

25:36.000 --> 25:39.834
I REMEMBER WHAT THE WONDERFUL
BOBBY DE NIRO ONCE SAID TO ME.

25:39.917 --> 25:42.667
WELL, NOT TO ME,
BUT I READ IT IN AN ARTICLE.

25:42.750 --> 25:45.375
AND IT WAS CONSIDERING
LANDING THE BIG ROLES,
AND WHAT HE SAID WAS,

25:45.458 --> 25:47.375
"JUST BECAUSE GOD BLESSES YOU,

25:47.458 --> 25:51.458
DOES NOT MEAN THERE ISN'T
ANOTHER SNEEZE COMING."

25:54.291 --> 25:57.500
ANYWAY, SEE YOU
AT THURSDAY'S REHEARSAL.

25:57.583 --> 25:58.750
YOU, TOO.

26:00.458 --> 26:04.542
UH, DR. FORREST OATES, THAT'S--
THAT'S KINDA GONNA BE A PROBLEM.

26:04.625 --> 26:08.125
SEE, NEXT WEEK WE GOT ALL
THE, UH, BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS.

26:11.125 --> 26:13.458
NOW, LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING,
BUB.

26:14.834 --> 26:17.083
THIS IS YOUR THEATRICAL DEBUT!

26:17.166 --> 26:19.166
I WANT YOU TO TAKE IT SERIOUSLY!

26:19.250 --> 26:23.667
I WANT YOU TO GIVE IT
HALF THE DEDICATION, JUST HALF

26:23.750 --> 26:25.041
THAT I GAVE MY OWN.

26:26.834 --> 26:30.959
TO BE OR NOT TO BE.
THAT IS THE QUESTION.

26:31.041 --> 26:33.792
[ Audience Cheering ]

26:36.792 --> 26:39.208
OH, THOSE WERE THE SALAD DAYS.

26:40.667 --> 26:42.166
ALTHOUGH THESE ARE GOOD.

26:43.542 --> 26:44.750
[ School Bell Rings ]

26:44.834 --> 26:48.583
THURSDAY, NONE OF THIS,
JOCK HEAD.

26:48.667 --> 26:50.834
[ Both Chuckle ]

26:53.667 --> 26:55.959
LET'S GO! JESSICA, WHAT--
WHY ARE YOU, LOOK-- WHAT--

26:56.041 --> 26:57.291
COME ON, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON.

26:57.375 --> 26:59.583
UH, EXCUSE ME, I'M A TEACHER.
THANKS.

26:59.667 --> 27:01.750
[ Whistle Blows ]

27:01.834 --> 27:03.000
LET'S GO, LET'S GO!

27:04.625 --> 27:06.291
WHERE ARE YOU GOIN', LANDERS?

27:07.417 --> 27:08.792
LANDERS!

27:08.875 --> 27:11.959
SO IN SUMMATION,
LYSANDER LOVES HERMIA,

27:12.041 --> 27:14.667
WHO LOVES LYSANDER,
BUT IS BETROTHED TO DEMETRIUS,

27:14.750 --> 27:17.750
WHO IN TURN IS THE OBJECT
OF HELENA'S AFFECTION.

27:17.834 --> 27:20.792
[ Laughing ]
NOW DO YOU SEE THE FUN OF IT?

27:20.875 --> 27:23.000
IT'S JUST ALL HELL
DONE BREAK LOOSE.

27:23.083 --> 27:25.834
MICKEY ROURKE SAID
A WONDERFUL THING
ABOUT HAVING FUN.

27:25.917 --> 27:29.083
HE WAS AT SOME BIG SOIREE THAT
LIZA MINNELLI WAS THROWING--

27:31.083 --> 27:34.625
MR. LANDERS,
HOW NICE OF YOU TO JOIN US.

27:34.709 --> 27:38.792
AND THANKS FOR NOT SHOWERING.
WHAT A SUPER INSTINCT.

27:38.875 --> 27:40.834
THE SECRET TO ALL THIS, YOU SEE,

27:40.917 --> 27:43.834
IS THAT OUR FOUR YOUNG LOVERS

27:43.917 --> 27:47.625
ARE NOT AS IN CONTROL
OF THEIR ROMANTIC DESTINIES
AS THEY THINK

27:47.709 --> 27:51.166
BECAUSE IN THE WOODS,
WE HAVE WHAT?

27:51.250 --> 27:53.333
FAIRIES.
FAIRIES! FAIRIES!

27:53.417 --> 27:55.166
SPIRITS! SPIRITS.

27:55.250 --> 27:57.166
[ Giggles ]

27:57.250 --> 28:01.792
SPECIFICALLY,
TITANIA, OBERON AND PUCK.

28:01.875 --> 28:04.000
LITTLE STEVE.
STEVEN.

28:04.083 --> 28:07.917
WHO DELIGHT IN MANIPULATING
THEIR HUMAN COUNTERPARTS...

28:08.959 --> 28:10.333
FOR SPORT.

28:10.417 --> 28:14.458
IT REALLY IS FUN TO SEE A
BUNCH OF FAIRIES BEING PLAYED--

28:15.583 --> 28:17.500
[ All Laughing ]

28:17.583 --> 28:19.709
HOLY SHIT, LITTLE STEVE,
YOU'VE GOT WINGS!

28:19.792 --> 28:22.208
YEAH, WELL, YOU'VE GOT FAIRY
DUST COMING OUT OF YOUR ASS.

28:22.291 --> 28:23.709
COME ON, GUYS.
LET'S STIR UP SOME TROUBLE.

28:23.792 --> 28:28.792
OH, FAIR HERMIA, THOU ART
SO INCREDIBLY HOT AND STUFF.

28:28.875 --> 28:33.083
HEY, RED, FOLLOW US.
YOU CAN'T SEE US,
BUT YOU'LL DO WHAT WE SAY.

28:33.166 --> 28:34.709
SUCKERS.

28:34.792 --> 28:36.417
[ Laughing ]

28:36.500 --> 28:38.834
YO, DUDE, SOMEBODY'S SCAMMIN'
ON YOUR CHICK.

28:38.917 --> 28:39.750
TIME TO KICK SOME ASS.

28:39.834 --> 28:40.875
[ Laughing ]

28:40.959 --> 28:41.875
[ Horse Whinnies ]

28:41.959 --> 28:44.875
DEMETRIUS, WHAT SAY YOU?

28:44.959 --> 28:46.542
RELENT, SWEET HERMIA.

28:46.625 --> 28:47.875
AND YOU, LYSANDER,

28:47.959 --> 28:50.875
YIELD THY CRAZED TITLE
TO MY CERTAIN RIGHT.

28:50.959 --> 28:53.875
EN GARDE.
WHAT? THERE'S NO SWORD FIGHTING
IN THIS PLAY.

28:53.959 --> 28:55.750
WELL, NOW THERE IS.

28:58.583 --> 29:01.458
[ Both Grunting ]

29:12.458 --> 29:14.083
[ Groaning ]

29:14.166 --> 29:16.583
OFF YOU GO.
OHH!

29:17.542 --> 29:19.709
[ Horse Whinnies ]

29:23.166 --> 29:25.375
[ Hermia Laughs ]
[ Demetrius Groans ]

29:25.458 --> 29:27.834
[ All Laughing ]

29:29.000 --> 29:30.917
WHEN IT RAINS, IT POURS.

29:31.000 --> 29:33.250
MR. LANDERS!
[ Chuckles ]

29:33.333 --> 29:35.709
[ Students Laughing ]
ARE WE HAVING R.E.M.?

29:42.834 --> 29:46.291
MUSICAL SHAKESPEARE?
CALLING MY SISTER?

29:46.375 --> 29:49.792
SHE'S HELPING ME OUT.
MY SISTER?

29:49.875 --> 29:50.917
YEAH.
SHE KNOWS WHAT SHE'S DOING.

29:51.000 --> 29:53.875
UH, WHATEVER. BERKE.
THIS ISN'T ABOUT HER, ALL RIGHT?

29:54.000 --> 29:56.834
THIS IS ABOUT YOU
RUNNING AFTER ALLISON.

29:56.917 --> 29:59.041
AND I'M SORRY,
BUT IT'S BULLSHIT.

30:00.000 --> 30:01.667
SEE YOU OUT THERE.

30:03.208 --> 30:05.792
THAT'S IT. WE GOTTA FIND OUR BOY
SOMEBODY, QUICK.

30:05.875 --> 30:08.583
YOU DON'T JUST ARBITRARILY
REPLACE SOMEONE'S SOUL MATE.

30:08.667 --> 30:10.959
I MEAN, LOOK AT THAT OLD LADY
FROM TITANIC.

30:11.041 --> 30:12.291
SHE DIDN'T NEVER GET OVER THAT.

30:12.375 --> 30:15.417
I'M NOT JUST TALKING
ABOUT ANYBODY.

30:15.500 --> 30:17.750
LOOK, YOU STILL TAKE SHOP
WITH DORA LYNN TISSDALE, RIGHT?

30:17.834 --> 30:22.750
YEAH. UM, LAST WEEK, SHE NEARLY
TOOK OUT HALF THE CLASS
WITH A NAIL GUN.

30:22.834 --> 30:24.792
SO SHE'S A BIT CLUMSY.

30:24.875 --> 30:26.417
THANKS TO GOOD OLD DORA LYNN,

30:26.500 --> 30:29.625
DICKIE BERGWELL
HAS TO TAKE A CRAP STANDING UP.

30:29.709 --> 30:32.125
DENNIS, WE'RE NOT ASKING HER

30:32.208 --> 30:34.959
TO BUILD AN APARTMENT COMPLEX,
ARE WE?

30:35.041 --> 30:36.542
AND WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
SHE'S GONNA DO IT?

30:36.625 --> 30:38.875
LOOK, THAT'S YOUR PROBLEM,
ALL RIGHT?

30:38.959 --> 30:40.667
I'LL TAKE CARE OF BERKE.

30:40.750 --> 30:45.375
DENNIS HEARD IT FIRSTHAND.
THE GIRL'S COMPLETELY INTO YOU.

30:45.458 --> 30:48.458
NO, THAT'S-- THAT'S BULLSHIT.
WHY WOULD I MAKE THIS UP?

30:48.542 --> 30:52.000
I MEAN, I'M PRESENTING YOU HERE
WITH A GOLDEN OPPORTUNITY,

30:52.083 --> 30:55.041
THE STANLEY CUP OF BLIND DATES,

30:55.125 --> 30:56.709
NEW ZEALAND'S GIFT
TO ROSNER HIGH.

30:56.792 --> 30:59.125
I MEAN, THOSE EYES,
THAT MOUTH, THE RACK.

30:59.208 --> 31:01.041
[ Berke ]
AREN'T YOU
FORGETTING SOMETHING?

31:01.125 --> 31:04.709
OHH!
[ Felix ]
OK, YEAH,
SHE'S A LITTLE ACCIDENT-PRONE.

31:04.792 --> 31:07.625
[ Berke ]
THE GIRL'S
A WALKING DISASTER ZONE.

31:07.709 --> 31:09.959
WHEREVER SHE GOES,
BAD SHIT HAPPENS.

31:10.041 --> 31:11.083
[ Girl ]
OH. OH, MY GOD!

31:11.166 --> 31:14.542
[ Berke ]
I MEAN, WEIRD BAD SHIT HAPPENS.

31:17.125 --> 31:18.583
[ Screaming ]

31:18.667 --> 31:22.041
SHE MISSED SIX YEARS
AT THE HIGH SCHOOL.

31:22.125 --> 31:25.041
SHE WAS IN A COMA
FOR CHRIST'S SAKES.
[ Groans ]

31:25.125 --> 31:27.250
BERKE, SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.
YEAH.

31:27.333 --> 31:29.000
SHE'S BUILT.
YEAH.

31:29.083 --> 31:31.250
AND APPARENTLY, SHE'S TOTALLY
WILLING TO LOWER HER STANDARDS,

31:31.333 --> 31:34.000
SO I REALLY DON'T SEE
ANYTHING WRONG WITH THIS.

31:37.458 --> 31:40.250
IT'S YOUR TURN TO GET THE BALL.

31:40.333 --> 31:42.917
I'M NOT GETTING THE BALL.
YOU GET THE BALL.

31:43.000 --> 31:44.959
[ Whines ]

31:47.792 --> 31:50.959
HEY, UH, DORA LYNN? DORA.

31:53.458 --> 31:54.875
KINDA GOT THIS FAVOR
TO A-- ASK YOU.
[ Yelling ]

31:54.959 --> 31:57.709
FAVOR? WHAT KIND OF FAVOR?
[ Yelling Continues ]

31:57.792 --> 32:00.166
[ Girl ]
JUST STOP, DROP, AND ROLL!

32:02.166 --> 32:04.959
BERKE, DON'T BE NERVOUS.

32:05.041 --> 32:08.583
I'M HERE BECAUSE I WANT TO BE.
ME, TOO.

32:08.667 --> 32:10.917
WE NEVER REALLY HAD A CHANCE
TO TALK.

32:11.000 --> 32:14.917
WELL, I THINK THAT HAD A LOT
TO DO WITH THE FACT THAT I WAS
BUSY WITH ALLISON

32:15.000 --> 32:18.875
AND YOU KINDA HAD YOUR
HANDS FULL WITH THE WHOLE, UH--

32:18.959 --> 32:20.750
COMA THING?
YEAH.

32:20.834 --> 32:22.792
YEAH.
YEAH.

32:22.875 --> 32:25.041
YOU KNOW, BERKE,

32:25.125 --> 32:27.291
IT'S ALL ABOUT NEW BEGINNINGS.

32:27.375 --> 32:30.917
THAT STUFF ABOUT ME BEING
BAD LUCK? ANCIENT HISTORY.

32:31.000 --> 32:35.542
I'M MOVING ON WITH MY LIFE,
AND YOU'RE MOVING ON WITH YOURS.

32:37.000 --> 32:39.083
[ Chuckles ]
SORRY.

32:39.166 --> 32:42.000
OH, WOULD YOU EXCUSE ME
FOR ONE MINUTE?

32:42.875 --> 32:44.500
I KINDA HAVE TO--

32:44.583 --> 32:46.417
PEE?
YEAH.

32:46.500 --> 32:48.667
OK.
OK.

32:48.750 --> 32:51.917
♪ [ "Hava Nagila":
Japanese Instrumentation ]

32:54.208 --> 32:56.917
WAITRESS,
CAN I HAVE SOME MORE TEA?

32:57.000 --> 32:58.083
OH, I LOVE--
AH!

32:59.166 --> 33:00.667
[ Groaning ]

33:00.750 --> 33:03.125
OHH!
TITS! WOW!

33:03.208 --> 33:05.917
[ Groaning ]

33:06.000 --> 33:07.166
[ Spits ]

33:09.208 --> 33:12.166
[ Patrons Gasping ]

33:12.250 --> 33:14.125
♪ [ Dissonant Chord ]

33:14.208 --> 33:16.959
OHH! OHH!

33:17.041 --> 33:18.750
[ Fire Alarm Bell Ringing ]

33:20.250 --> 33:22.709
[ Shouting In Japanese ]

33:23.959 --> 33:25.583
CHECK, PLEASE!

33:27.625 --> 33:31.166
♪ I'M DREAMING OF A BOY
A VERY SPECIAL GUY ♪

33:31.250 --> 33:35.375
♪ I WISH THAT I COULD PLUCK
A FAIRY FROM THE SKY ♪

33:35.458 --> 33:39.333
♪ TO CAST A SPELL
UPON MY PRIDE AND JOY ♪

33:39.417 --> 33:41.792
♪ I'M DREAMING
OF A VERY SPECIAL BOY ♪

33:41.875 --> 33:43.208
TIME. TIME.

33:43.291 --> 33:46.166
[ Chuckling ]
IT'S JUST NOT VERY GOOD.

33:46.250 --> 33:49.000
I COULD LIE TO YOU,
BUT I WOULD DO YOU A DISSERVICE

33:49.083 --> 33:51.834
BECAUSE IT'S-- IT'S JUST BAD.
YOU'VE GOT TO COMMIT.

33:51.917 --> 33:56.667
[ Belting ]
♪ I'M DREAMING OF A BOY
A VERY SPECIAL GUY ♪

33:56.750 --> 34:00.333
AND THEN, "I WISH
THAT I COULD PLUCK, PLUCK!
I WANNA SEE YOU PLUCK IT!

34:00.417 --> 34:02.834
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?
WE'LL TALK ABOUT IT LATER.

34:02.917 --> 34:04.875
OK, ENTER THESEUS.

34:04.959 --> 34:09.250
NOW, ATTENDANTS,
A ROGUE SUITOR...

34:09.333 --> 34:12.208
IS SPOONING
WITH THE MASTER'S DAUGHTER.

34:12.291 --> 34:14.208
WELL,
THIS IS TOTALLY SCANDALOUS.

34:14.291 --> 34:17.208
SO YOU MUST LOOK SHOCKED,
YOU MUST LOOK AMAZED.

34:17.291 --> 34:18.625
LET'S SEE YOU LOOK SHOCKED.

34:20.333 --> 34:23.041
I SAID SHOCKED, MR. LANDERS,
NOT CONSTIPATED.

34:23.125 --> 34:24.833
[ All Laughing ]

34:24.917 --> 34:27.500
OH, MY DEAR GOD. GO, DEL.

34:29.291 --> 34:32.375
GO BID THE HUNTSMEN.
WAKE THEM WITH THEIR HORNS.

34:32.458 --> 34:35.083
HOLD IT. YES, UM--

34:35.166 --> 34:36.166
UM, WELL, CAN I--

34:36.250 --> 34:38.208
YOU'D TELL ME
IF YOU'D HAD A STROKE.

34:38.291 --> 34:40.083
♪ [ Piano ]

34:40.166 --> 34:44.250
[ Woman ]
AND EIGHT.
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR--

34:44.333 --> 34:47.250
WHAT?
WHAT?

34:47.333 --> 34:49.417
ARE YOU LOST?

34:49.500 --> 34:53.458
UM, NO. ACTUALLY, I-- I SIGNED
UP FOR STAGE CREW, AND I--

34:53.542 --> 34:56.875
STAGE CREW? THEN SHOULDN'T YOU
BE OVER THERE?

34:58.333 --> 35:00.542
[ Moaning ]
OH.

35:02.709 --> 35:03.875
OH, RIGHT.

35:06.166 --> 35:09.583
MY LORD, I SHALL REPLY AMAZEDLY.

35:09.667 --> 35:12.583
HALF SLEEP, HALF WAKEN,
I CAME WITH HERMIA HITHER.

35:12.667 --> 35:16.083
OUR INTENT WAS TO BE GONE
FROM ATHENS,

35:16.166 --> 35:20.917
WHERE WE MIGHT, WITHOUT
THE PERIL OF ATHENIAN LAW,

35:21.000 --> 35:22.417
BE WED.

35:22.500 --> 35:26.250
AH-AH-AH.
SAVE IT FOR SHOW NIGHT, WONG.

35:26.333 --> 35:27.583
SORRY, STRIKER.

35:27.667 --> 35:30.583
♪

35:39.041 --> 35:42.667
♪ WHAT DO YOU GET
WHEN YOU FALL IN LOVE? ♪

35:42.750 --> 35:46.458
♪ A GIRL WITH A PIN
TO BURST YOUR BUBBLE ♪

35:46.542 --> 35:50.291
♪ THAT'S WHAT YOU GET
FOR ALL YOUR TROUBLE ♪

35:50.375 --> 35:52.125
♪ I'LL ♪

35:52.208 --> 35:56.834
♪ NEVER FALL IN LOVE AGAIN ♪

35:58.208 --> 36:00.458
♪ I'LL NEVER FALL IN LOVE ♪

36:00.542 --> 36:04.125
♪ WHAT DO YOU GET
WHEN YOU KISS A GIRL? ♪

36:04.208 --> 36:06.291
♪ [ Continues ]
YOU KNOW WHAT?

36:06.375 --> 36:08.333
I'D ASK YOU WHAT THE HELL
YOU'RE EVEN DOING HERE,

36:08.417 --> 36:11.792
BUT IF SOME STRANGER HAD DAZZLED
HIS WAY INTO MY EX-GIRLFRIEND'S
FANCIES,

36:11.875 --> 36:14.542
I'D PROBABLY BE
DOING THE SAME THING,

36:14.625 --> 36:16.875
ONLY I'D HAVE A BIGGER PART.

36:17.959 --> 36:19.166
YOU DROPPED YOUR SWORD.

36:19.250 --> 36:22.875
♪ I'LL NEVER FALL IN LOVE
AGAIN ♪

36:24.417 --> 36:27.375
[ Whistle Blows ]
♪ DON'T TELL ME WHAT IT'S ALL ♪

36:27.458 --> 36:29.208
♪ ABOUT ♪

36:29.291 --> 36:33.208
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE BEEN THERE
AND I'M GLAD I'M OUT ♪

36:33.291 --> 36:36.709
♪ OUT OF THOSE CHAINS
THOSE CHAINS THAT BIND YOU ♪
I AM SO SORRY. BIG-- BIG GAME.

36:36.792 --> 36:40.792
♪ AND THAT IS WHAT
I'M HERE TO REMIND YOU ♪

36:40.875 --> 36:42.166
♪ [ Continues ]

36:42.250 --> 36:45.667
SUBSTITUTION.
SORRY, SIR.
THERE WAS A BIG ACCIDENT.

36:45.750 --> 36:48.041
YOU ARE SO LUCKY
I AM NOT BOBBY KNIGHT.

36:48.125 --> 36:50.500
AND WE GOT PLAYOFFS NEXT WEEK
AND YOU'VE GOT AN OBLIGATION
TO THE TEAM.

36:50.583 --> 36:52.834
NOW GET OUT THERE!
YES, SIR!

36:52.917 --> 36:56.208
[ Man On Speaker ]
SUBSTITUTION FOR ROSNER,
BERKE LANDERS.

36:56.291 --> 36:58.917
[ All Laughing ]

37:00.333 --> 37:03.417
HEY, LANDERS, NICE ASS!

37:06.125 --> 37:07.250
I'M GONNA GO NOW.

37:07.333 --> 37:10.000
♪ NEVER FALL IN LOVE AGAIN ♪

37:10.083 --> 37:12.500
[ Whistle Blows ]

37:12.583 --> 37:15.166
[ Berke ]
YEAH, I'LL SEE YOU GUYS LATER.
HAVE A GOOD NIGHT.

37:15.250 --> 37:18.125
♪ [ Piano ]

37:28.500 --> 37:30.542
DON'T STOP BECAUSE OF ME.

37:30.625 --> 37:34.667
SORRY. I-- I JUST NEVER GET
TO PLAY A REAL PIANO AT HOME.

37:37.375 --> 37:40.625
SO YOU'VE BEEN A BUSY GUY
LATELY.

37:40.709 --> 37:43.875
YEAH, DATING A PYROMANIAC,
SHOWING MY ASS IN PUBLIC.

37:43.959 --> 37:46.709
WELL, IT'S ALL
IN THE NAME OF LOVE, RIGHT?

37:48.208 --> 37:49.375
RIGHT.

37:53.333 --> 37:55.291
PLAY ME SOMETHING.

37:56.709 --> 37:59.375
NO.
COME ON. IT SOUNDED GOOD.

37:59.458 --> 38:00.792
I'M EMBARRASSED.

38:02.959 --> 38:06.250
I LOVE WRITING SONGS,
BUT IT-- [ Sighs ]

38:06.333 --> 38:07.417
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

38:07.500 --> 38:10.250
WELL, YOU WERE AT THE AUDITION,
BERKE.

38:10.333 --> 38:12.208
FORREST OATES HATED MY SONG.

38:12.875 --> 38:14.625
WELL,

38:14.709 --> 38:18.083
I ADMIRED YOU
FOR PUTTING YOURSELF
OUT THERE LIKE THAT,

38:18.166 --> 38:21.458
AND, UH, YOU KNOW,
FOR WHATEVER IT'S WORTH,

38:21.542 --> 38:24.583
I-- I-- I THOUGHT IT WAS
A REALLY NICE SONG.

38:27.166 --> 38:28.333
THANKS.

38:32.375 --> 38:34.542
THIS IS A SONG I WROTE.

38:35.709 --> 38:37.083
♪ [ Picking Out Notes ]
♪ B, C ♪

38:37.166 --> 38:39.959
♪ D, E, F, G ♪
OH, GOD!
[ Giggles ]

38:41.875 --> 38:43.792
BRING IT ON.

38:43.875 --> 38:48.333
[ Together ]
♪ H, I, J, K, L, M, N, O, P ♪

38:51.583 --> 38:54.542
♪ [ Continues Full Chords ]

38:56.917 --> 38:58.041
SHOWOFF.

39:22.125 --> 39:23.959
[ Phone Rings ]

39:24.750 --> 39:26.500
BERKE.
YEAH. HEY, FELIX.

39:26.583 --> 39:29.458
HOW DO YOU FEEL
ABOUT HALF-NAKED WOMEN?

39:29.542 --> 39:32.166
♪ [ Techno Dance ]
WOULD YOU MIND TELLING ME
WHERE WE'RE GOING?

39:32.250 --> 39:35.041
SUFFICE TO SAY, DENNIS AND I,
WE DISCUSSED IT

39:35.125 --> 39:37.000
AND DECIDED THAT
THIS IS EXACTLY WHAT YOU NEED.

39:37.083 --> 39:41.333
[ Woman On Loudspeaker ]
IT LOOKS LIKE WE HAVE A VERY
SPECIAL GUEST WITH US TONIGHT,

39:41.417 --> 39:46.625
A YOUNG MAN RECENTLY JILTED
BY HIS LONGTIME LADY LOVE.

39:48.458 --> 39:50.792
HEY, SEE YOU LATER, CASANOVA.

39:53.625 --> 39:55.959
OHH!
[ Laughs ]

40:02.000 --> 40:03.875
YEAH.
WHAT'S THAT?

40:03.959 --> 40:06.375
[ Woman On Loudspeaker ]
IT'S MONDAY MADNESS, PEOPLE.

40:06.458 --> 40:08.834
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS.

40:11.458 --> 40:13.792
♪ [ Drums ]

40:15.583 --> 40:17.250
[ Laughs ]

40:18.458 --> 40:22.041
BEHOLD MY MAJESTIC,
CORSETED FORM!

40:22.125 --> 40:26.625
POLICE!
I WANT TO SEE SOME IDS,
AND I WANT TO SEE THEM QUICK!

40:26.709 --> 40:28.041
OH, MY GOD!
SORRY!

40:28.125 --> 40:30.834
[ Patrons, Strippers Scream,
Shout ]

40:39.834 --> 40:43.333
HEY, CAN SOMEBODY
GET ME DOWN? PLEASE?

40:44.667 --> 40:47.208
JESUS, MOTHER OF GOD!

40:48.875 --> 40:50.917
I MUST SAY,
YOU SURPRISED US, BERKE.

40:51.000 --> 40:53.041
IT'S NOT EVERY DAY
YOU GET A WAKE-UP CALL
FROM THE COPS

40:53.125 --> 40:55.959
SAYING YOUR SON'S BEEN PINCHED
IN A SEX CLUB RAID.

40:56.041 --> 40:59.125
THAT SAID, YOUR FATHER AND I
HAVE DISCUSSED IT--

40:59.208 --> 41:03.792
AND WE'D JUST LIKE TO SAY--
WE ARE
SO INCREDIBLY PROUD OF YOU.

41:03.875 --> 41:04.542
WHAT?

41:04.625 --> 41:06.834
FOR GETTING ON WITH YOUR LIFE.

41:06.917 --> 41:10.500
MOST KIDS YOUR AGE
ARE WAY ILL-EQUIPPED
TO DEAL WITH HEARTACHE.

41:10.583 --> 41:13.458
BUT NOT YOU, MISTER.
YOU GOT RIGHT BACK
ON THAT HORSE.

41:13.542 --> 41:15.834
OR SHOULD I SAY,
SUSPENSION HARNESS?
STOP IT.

41:15.917 --> 41:19.667
MOM, DAD, I JUST GOT ARRESTED.
SHOULDN'T YOU BE, LIKE,
PISSED OR SOMETHING?

41:19.750 --> 41:23.458
WHY? SEXUAL CURIOSITY
IS PERFECTLY NATURAL.

41:23.542 --> 41:25.667
WE JUST HAD NO IDEA
YOU WERE SO KINKY.
YEAH.

41:25.750 --> 41:27.625
HEY, WHO'S UP
FOR FROZEN YOGURT?

41:27.709 --> 41:29.625
OOH, SOUNDS GOOD TO ME.

41:29.709 --> 41:34.500
WELL, THEN AGAIN,
BERKE MAY WANT TO GO HOME
AND POLISH THE ROCKET.

41:34.583 --> 41:37.625
YOGURT'S GOOD.
[ Techno Music ]

41:38.917 --> 41:40.041
OK.

41:42.208 --> 41:43.375
OK, DENNIS.

41:43.959 --> 41:46.125
WHAT?
BRING HER UP.

41:49.375 --> 41:51.291
[ Grunting, Giggling ]

41:52.750 --> 41:54.667
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

41:54.750 --> 41:57.875
INTRODUCING
PRISONER NUMBER 6943.

41:57.959 --> 42:00.625
BRAVO, LANDERS, BRAVO.

42:00.709 --> 42:03.458
YOU KNOW, YOU DO TAKE
A STUNNING PICTURE.

42:03.542 --> 42:06.333
[ Chuckles ]
STRIKER, I'D BE CAREFUL
ABOUT THAT ACCENT

42:06.417 --> 42:09.375
BECAUSE YOU'RE BEGINNING TO
SOUND A LOT LIKE MARY POPPINS.

42:09.458 --> 42:12.291
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE BLATHERING ABOUT,
BUT IF I WERE YOU--

42:12.375 --> 42:13.959
HOLD IT, HOLD IT, HOLD IT.

42:15.583 --> 42:17.458
WHAT?
ARE YOU WEARING MAKEUP?

42:20.542 --> 42:22.166
THAT'S IT.

42:22.250 --> 42:23.667
[ Woman ]
OH.

42:23.750 --> 42:25.750
OOH.
[ Striker Grunts ]

42:25.834 --> 42:29.917
CAREFUL, LANDERS.
I DO BELIEVE YOU ARE
TRIFLING WITH DANGER.

42:30.000 --> 42:32.750
WHO KEEPS NUNCHUCKS
IN THEIR PANTS?

42:34.834 --> 42:35.667
OHH!
[ Groans ]

42:35.750 --> 42:37.375
[ Peter Groans ]

42:37.458 --> 42:39.458
PETER WONG IS DOWN!

42:41.917 --> 42:43.709
LOOK ON THE BRIGHT SIDE, WONG.

42:43.792 --> 42:45.667
YOU'RE A SINGER, NOT A DANCER.

42:45.750 --> 42:49.875
I'LL KILL YOU,
YOU ANT-KISSING, PRETENTIOUS,
SWING TOWN TWIT!

42:49.959 --> 42:54.166
THIS IS MY THEATER!
MY SHOW!

42:54.250 --> 42:57.166
FORREST OATES
IS MY SPECIAL BUDDY!

42:57.250 --> 42:59.041
THAT WAS INTENSE.
[ Peter Wailing ]

42:59.125 --> 43:03.083
I KNOW. I'VE NEVER SEEN BONE
POKE THROUGH SKIN LIKE THAT
BEFORE.

43:03.166 --> 43:07.750
ALL RIGHT THEN, EVERYTHING'S
GOING TO BE FINE,
ACCORDING TO THE PARAMEDICS.
[ Wailing Continues ]

43:07.834 --> 43:10.792
IN FACT, PETER WILL BE
BACK ON HIS FEET IN NO TIME.

43:10.875 --> 43:14.583
[ Peter Shrieks ]

43:14.667 --> 43:17.542
STILL, IN THE WORDS
OF THE WONDERFUL KEVIN SPACEY,

43:17.625 --> 43:19.291
THE SHOW MUST GO ON.

43:19.375 --> 43:21.792
SO SINCE CURTAIN IS,
INDEED, IN THREE DAYS,

43:21.875 --> 43:26.375
I'M NOW ACCEPTING OFFERS
FROM VOLUNTEERS
FOR THE ROLE OF LYSANDER.

43:26.458 --> 43:27.166
OOH! OOH!

43:27.250 --> 43:28.792
PUT YOUR HAND DOWN,
LITTLE STEVE!

43:28.875 --> 43:30.417
OOH.

43:30.500 --> 43:32.208
NO, NOT STRIKER,
YOU ALREADY HAVE A ROLE.

43:32.291 --> 43:36.792
YES, I KNOW, BUT I WAS WANTING
TO NOMINATE SOMEONE.

43:36.875 --> 43:41.375
[ Chuckling ]
OH, WELL, THAT'S VERY
FLATTERING, UH, INDEED,

43:41.458 --> 43:46.125
BUT I DON'T THINK A MAN OF 34
CAN POSSIBLY KEEP UP
WITH YOU YOUNGSTERS.

43:46.208 --> 43:48.792
ACTUALLY, I WAS REFERRING TO...

43:48.875 --> 43:50.834
BERKE LANDERS.

43:50.917 --> 43:52.333
[ Students Murmuring ]

43:52.417 --> 43:53.792
OH! WELL, TH--

43:53.875 --> 43:56.792
THAT'S AN INTRIGUING THOUGHT.

43:56.875 --> 43:57.959
ANY OTHER IDEAS?

43:58.041 --> 43:59.333
OOH!
ONE THAT I MIGHT USE?

43:59.417 --> 44:00.959
PUT YOUR HAND DOWN,
LITTLE STEVE!

44:01.041 --> 44:03.625
WELL, HE'S GREEN, TO BE SURE,
BUT HE DOES DEMONSTRATE

44:03.709 --> 44:06.083
A CERTAIN... ENTHUSIASM.

44:07.667 --> 44:10.125
I'M IN.
[ Students Gasp ]

44:10.208 --> 44:12.417
YOU'RE IN?
YEAH, I'M IN.

44:14.041 --> 44:16.625
JESSICA, CALL DOMINO'S.
WE'LL BE HERE A WHILE.

44:16.709 --> 44:19.625
AND KEEP ICING YOUR FRONT BUM!

44:19.709 --> 44:23.083
SWELLING CONTINUES
WHEN YOU DON'T ICE,
AND I NEED YOU.

44:24.208 --> 44:26.667
NOT REALLY.
[ Guitar Music ]

44:26.750 --> 44:28.166
SO HOW MANY SWORDS DO WE HAVE?

44:28.250 --> 44:31.500
SEVEN.
EIGHT.

44:31.583 --> 44:35.291
I SWEAR, IF ALLISON
DOESN'T APPRECIATE THIS--
THEN WHAT?

44:37.375 --> 44:39.875
ANYWAY, I'VE HEARD YOU
DO THE DIALOGUE. YOU'RE FINE.

44:39.959 --> 44:43.542
YEAH, BUT WHAT ABOUT
THE SINGING?
WELL, THE MUSIC SUCKS.

44:43.625 --> 44:44.583
ESPECIALLY MY SONG.

44:44.667 --> 44:47.166
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU,
WHY DON'T YOU REWRITE IT?

44:47.250 --> 44:49.834
OH, FORREST OATES
WOULD NEVER GO FOR IT.

44:49.917 --> 44:54.000
KELLY, YOU'RE THE BEST ONE
IN THE PLAY. YOU KNOW MORE
ABOUT THIS STUFF THAN HE DOES.

44:54.083 --> 44:57.458
YEAH, BUT HE DOESN'T SEE IT
THAT WAY.

44:57.542 --> 44:59.834
FORREST OATES
JUST CAST ME AS A LEAD.

44:59.917 --> 45:02.083
HE'S AN IDIOT, ALLISON.

45:04.792 --> 45:06.834
MY NAME...

45:06.917 --> 45:08.834
IS KELLY.

45:08.917 --> 45:10.875
WHAT'D I SAY?
ALLISON.

45:10.959 --> 45:12.709
NO, I DIDN'T.
YEAH, YOU DID.

45:12.792 --> 45:14.917
I'M SORRY.
PREPARE TO DIE.

45:15.000 --> 45:18.041
MAYBE Y-- YOU SHOULDN'T
BE PLAYING WITH THAT.

45:18.125 --> 45:20.166
PUT-- COM--
PUT IT DOWN.

45:20.917 --> 45:23.291
PUT IT-- K-- KELLY.

45:26.917 --> 45:28.041
AAAAH!

45:28.125 --> 45:29.417
WE HAVE AN 18-YEAR-OLD
WHITE MALE

45:29.500 --> 45:31.709
WITH AN ANTERIOR PUNCTURE WOUND
TO HIS LEFT ARM.

45:31.792 --> 45:35.417
MY GOD, I'M SO SORRY, BERKE.
I THOUGHT IT WAS A PROP.
I WANNA SEE IT.

45:35.500 --> 45:38.166
NO, DON'T LOOK AT IT.
IT'S PRETTY BAD, ISN'T IT?

45:38.250 --> 45:41.875
NO, IT'S-- IT'S FINE.
HERE, LISTEN TO ME, BERKE.

45:41.959 --> 45:44.208
THE DOCTOR'S GONNA FIX YOUR ARM
AND I'M GONNA HELP YOU REHEARSE

45:44.291 --> 45:46.875
AND YOU'RE GONNA BE
THE BEST LYSANDER EVER, OK?

45:46.959 --> 45:49.875
AND YOUR ARM,
IT'S REALLY NOT THAT--
OH, MY GOD! OHH!

