DAH-DE-DAH ♪

46:40.208 --> 46:43.625
♪ FORTY-EIGHT HOURS
I'M STILL HAVIN' IT BAD ♪

46:43.709 --> 46:45.959
♪ THIRTY-TWO TO GO
I WAS VIRTUALLY DEAD ♪

46:46.041 --> 46:47.959
♪ MAKIN' A MESS
ON SOMEONE'S DESK ♪

46:48.041 --> 46:51.291
♪ I DID IT AGAIN
BAH-DAH-DAH-DAH DAH-DAH ♪

46:51.375 --> 46:54.125
♪ STARTED LOOKIN' FOR SOMEONE
THE KIND IS YOU ♪

46:54.208 --> 46:56.166
♪ ALL THE OTHER PLACES WERE
THERE ARE NOTHIN' TO DO ♪

46:56.250 --> 46:58.959
♪ SO WASTE THE MORNING
AND HANG IN BED
NOBODY CARES ♪

46:59.041 --> 47:02.959
SO WHEN DO YOUR PARENTS LEAVE
FOR THIS AFFILIATE STUFF?
UH, TODAY.

47:03.041 --> 47:05.291
DON'T EVEN THINK ABOUT IT.
WHAT?

47:05.375 --> 47:08.500
FELIX, I CAN HEAR YOUR BRAIN
PLANNING A PARTY. NO.

47:08.583 --> 47:12.166
I'LL-- I'LL SEE YOU GUYS LA--
I GOTTA GET SOMETHING.

47:12.250 --> 47:14.583
HEY, WHY IS HE GOING
INTO THE MUSIC STORE?
I DON'T KNOW.

47:14.667 --> 47:17.208
HE'S PROBABLY BUYING TAP SHOES
OR SOME SHIT LIKE THAT,

47:17.291 --> 47:20.333
WHICH ONLY FURTHER DEMONSTRATES
MY POINT, MY FRIEND.

47:20.417 --> 47:24.667
THAT MAN IS IN DIRE NEED
OF A PARTY.
[ Loud Slurping ]

47:24.750 --> 47:26.375
[ Knock On Door ]
YES?

47:26.458 --> 47:29.875
HI. I KNOW YOU'RE BUSY,
BUT I JUST WANNA TALK TO YOU
FOR ONE SECOND.

47:29.959 --> 47:33.125
OH, MISS WOODS,
PLEASE COME IN-- OHH.

47:33.208 --> 47:37.000
FUN HAIR CLIP.
HMM.

47:37.083 --> 47:39.041
I WANTED TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT MY SONG.

47:39.125 --> 47:40.667
OH, "POCKETFUL OF DREAMS."

47:40.750 --> 47:44.542
I ORIGINALLY WROTE THAT TUNE
FOR MISS DIANA ROSS.

47:46.291 --> 47:47.458
♪ [ Disco ]
MISS ROSS! MISS ROSS!

47:47.542 --> 47:49.000
I'VE WRITTEN
A VERY GROOVY SONG!

47:49.083 --> 47:50.625
I THINK YOU'D LI-- OH!

47:50.709 --> 47:54.000
THAT'S MY HAND, BUDDY!
AAH! MISS ROSS!

47:54.083 --> 47:58.083
MISS ROSS! DIANA!

47:58.166 --> 48:01.041
UNFORTUNATELY,
THE LAWYERS GOT INVOLVED,

48:01.125 --> 48:04.250
AND THEN BULLSHIT, BULLSHIT,
BULLSHIT, BULLSHIT.

48:04.333 --> 48:09.000
AND THEN, UH,
THE NEXT THING YOU KNOW--
PHTT! NO DEAL.

48:09.083 --> 48:13.041
IT'S A GREAT SONG.
I LOVE SINGING IT.
OH, IT WAS FUN TO WRITE.

48:13.125 --> 48:17.041
IT'S JUST THAT I WAS WONDERING
IF YOU-- IF YOU WOULDN'T MIND...

48:17.125 --> 48:19.166
IF I MADE A FEW SUGGESTIONS.

48:19.250 --> 48:21.792
YOU'VE MADE
S-- SOME SUGGESTIONS?

48:22.959 --> 48:24.083
"O WEARY NIGHT,

48:24.166 --> 48:26.250
ABATE THY HOURS."

48:26.333 --> 48:31.875
WELL, I-- I JUST FIGURED,
YOU KNOW, LIKE YOU SAID,
THE SONG REALLY ISN'T WORKING.

48:31.959 --> 48:33.583
[ Chuckling ]

48:33.667 --> 48:36.750
I'D LIKE YOU TO DO ME A FAVOR,
IF YOU WILL, MISS WOODS.

48:36.834 --> 48:40.291
I'D LIKE YOU TO READ THIS POSTER
AND TELL ME
WHAT IT SAYS AT THE BOTTOM.

48:40.375 --> 48:43.125
"NO FOOD OR DRINK ALLOWED
IN THE AUDITORIUM AT ANY TIME."

48:43.208 --> 48:46.083
IT SAYS, "12 ORIGINAL SONGS

48:46.166 --> 48:48.250
BY DR. DESMOND FORREST OATES."

48:48.333 --> 48:52.750
OH. [ Chuckles ]
THAT PART.
YES, THAT PART.

48:52.834 --> 48:54.083
I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT IT DOESN'T SAY.

48:54.166 --> 48:55.291
IT DOESN'T SAY,
"ADDITIONAL LYRICS

48:55.375 --> 48:58.083
BY LITTLE MISS SASSY-PANTS."

48:58.166 --> 48:59.917
YOU KNOW, SOME OF THOSE LYRICS
ARE SHAKESPEARE'S.

49:00.000 --> 49:04.542
AH. AND WHAT WAS THE LAST TUNE
YOU HUMMED FROM MACBETH?

49:04.625 --> 49:07.458
BILL SHAKESPEARE
IS A WONDERFUL POET,

49:07.542 --> 49:10.500
BUT BURT BACHARACH, HE AIN'T.

49:11.166 --> 49:12.750
[ Whispers ]
I'LL GO.

49:12.834 --> 49:14.709
SORRY I'M LATE.
THAT'S-- THAT'S OK.

49:14.792 --> 49:16.959
I WAS JUST GETTING LUCKY.
OH, CHESTER!

49:17.041 --> 49:20.083
WE NEED-- WE NEED-- WE NEED--
WE NEED TO FIND THIS DOG A DATE.

49:20.166 --> 49:24.500
[ Growls ]
SO, UH, HOW WAS--
HOW WAS FORREST OATES?

49:24.583 --> 49:27.125
A BIGGER ASSHOLE THAN I THOUGHT.

49:27.208 --> 49:31.792
MAYBE THIS WILL MAKE YOU
FEEL A LITTLE BETTER.
OH, A GIFT? BERKE.

49:31.875 --> 49:35.125
FIRST WE REHEARSE, OK?

49:35.208 --> 49:36.750
OK.
ALL RIGHT.

49:40.583 --> 49:46.125
[ Both ]
♪ SO THAT'S THE GIRL
THAT I'VE GOT TO HAVE ♪

49:46.208 --> 49:48.917
♪ I'LL TELL YOU WHY-- ♪

49:49.000 --> 49:50.208
♪ [ Keyboard Off ]

49:51.041 --> 49:53.500
IT'S 21 HOURS UNTIL THE PLAY,

49:53.583 --> 49:55.750
AND I'M ACTUALLY
STARTING TO SUCK MORE.

49:55.834 --> 49:59.333
LOOK, LET'S JUST PUT THE SONGS
ASIDE FOR A SECOND.

49:59.417 --> 50:01.166
WE'LL WORK ON SOME DIALOGUE.

50:01.250 --> 50:05.500
WE'RE AT THE POINT
WHERE THESEUS HAS JUST
WOKEN EVERYBODY UP.

50:05.583 --> 50:06.875
ALL RIGHT.

50:12.625 --> 50:13.542
HI.
HI.

50:15.291 --> 50:17.250
[ Both Chuckling ]

50:18.458 --> 50:22.166
OK, THIS SCENE'S
BETWEEN YOU AND HERMIA.

50:22.250 --> 50:25.333
SO PRETEND I'M ALLISON, OK?
SURE.

50:25.417 --> 50:28.166
AS DIFFICULT AS THAT MIGHT BE.

50:28.250 --> 50:29.917
NO, GO AHEAD.

50:32.125 --> 50:35.625
SO THESEUS SAYS,

50:35.709 --> 50:38.834
"GO, WAKE THEM
WITH THEIR HORNS."

50:38.917 --> 50:41.166
AND HERMIA SAYS,

50:41.250 --> 50:45.250
"METHINKS I SEE THINGS
WITH PARTED EYE,

50:45.333 --> 50:47.458
WHEN EVERYTHING SEEMS DOUBLE."

50:50.625 --> 50:51.583
OK, I GOT IT.

50:51.667 --> 50:58.041
UH, MY LORD,
I REPLY AMAZEDLY,

50:58.125 --> 51:01.125
HALF ASLEEP, HALF AWAKE.

51:02.458 --> 51:05.041
I CAME WITH HERMIA HITHER.

51:05.125 --> 51:07.375
[ Both Chuckle]

51:07.458 --> 51:12.875
OUR INTENT IS TO LEAVE ATHENS...
MM-HMM.

51:12.959 --> 51:14.917
WHERE WE MAY BE MARRIED.

51:16.250 --> 51:19.208
AND THEN THERE'S THE KISS...

51:19.291 --> 51:21.417
WHICH IS GONNA BE WITH ALLISON.

51:21.500 --> 51:22.667
RIGHT.

51:24.792 --> 51:26.917
BUT IN THIS CASE--

51:32.375 --> 51:34.417
[ Phone Rings ]

51:34.500 --> 51:36.625
[ Sighs ]
SHIT.

51:36.709 --> 51:38.625
WHAT?
HEY, LET ME TAKE A SHOT
IN THE DARK.

51:38.709 --> 51:41.917
BERKE'S THERE, RIGHT?
FELIX, WHERE ARE YOU?

51:42.000 --> 51:43.750
BIG PARTY. HEY, LISTEN.

51:43.834 --> 51:46.291
TELL, UH, TELL BERKE HE MIGHT
WANNA STOP BY

51:46.375 --> 51:49.417
BECAUSE THERE'S SOME, UH, PEOPLE
WHO'VE BEEN ASKING ABOUT HIM.

51:49.500 --> 51:50.417
WE GOTTA GO TO YOUR HOUSE.

51:50.500 --> 51:52.250
♪ [ Stereo: Dance Pop ]

51:52.333 --> 51:54.625
WELL, WELL. I'M IMPRESSED.

51:54.709 --> 51:57.417
TURNOUT'S NOT HALF-BAD.
WHERE'S FELIX?

51:57.500 --> 51:59.875
DUDE, UH, YOU SHOULD
REALLY BREATHE, MAN.

51:59.959 --> 52:01.792
I MEAN, YOU LOOK LIKE
YOU'RE GONNA STROKE OUT.

52:01.875 --> 52:04.083
LOOK, I'M GONNA LOOK
FOR HIM OVER HERE, OK?

52:04.166 --> 52:07.041
YOU REALIZE
I'M GOING TO KILL HIM.

52:07.125 --> 52:08.208
FELIX!

52:10.542 --> 52:13.125
FELIX!
IF IT ISN'T MY BEAUTEOUS COSTAR.

52:13.208 --> 52:15.834
HAVE YOU SEEN
MY BROTHER FELIX?
FAIR HELENA.

52:15.917 --> 52:20.291
SO TENSE. A FEW
PRE-SHOW JITTERS, PERHAPS?

52:20.375 --> 52:24.917
OR MAYBE SOME LOVE PANGS
FOR A CERTAIN YOU-KNOW-WHO.

52:25.000 --> 52:26.959
YOU!
BERKE! WHAT'S UP?

52:27.041 --> 52:30.125
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK, HUH?
WHAT DO I THINK?
WHAT DO I THINK?

52:30.208 --> 52:31.333
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

52:31.417 --> 52:32.500
FRANKLY, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU GIRLS SEE

52:32.583 --> 52:34.750
IN THIS UNDEREDUCATED WANK.

52:34.834 --> 52:39.625
PERHAPS YOU CAN TAKE ME
OUT TO THE VERANDA AND...

52:39.709 --> 52:40.458
EDIFY ME.

52:40.542 --> 52:42.583
SHIT, IT'S STRIKER.

52:42.667 --> 52:46.125
LOOK, I'LL SEE YOU AT THE SHOW.
WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON?

52:46.208 --> 52:48.750
NOTHING.
JUST A BIT OF TOMFOOLERY.

52:48.834 --> 52:52.500
FELIX, I'M HANDLING IT.
NO, YOU'RE BEING HANDLED
BY LEATHER PANTS HERE.

52:52.583 --> 52:54.875
THERE'S A DIFFERENCE.
I THINK YOU BETTER GO.

52:54.959 --> 52:57.291
OH, COME ON. DO YOU REALLY THINK
I'D FOOL AROUND ON ALLISON?

52:57.375 --> 53:00.333
YOU, OF ALL PEOPLE, SHOULD KNOW
HOW DAMNABLE THAT WOULD BE.

53:00.417 --> 53:02.125
NOW, WHERE'S THE GRUB?
THIS WAY? THANK YOU.

53:02.208 --> 53:05.125
♪ [ Dance ]
[ People Chattering, Laughing ]

53:11.917 --> 53:14.333
[ Grunts ]
GUYS.

53:14.417 --> 53:17.375
IS IT JUST ME OR DOES THIS PUNCH
TASTE KIND OF FUNKY?

53:17.458 --> 53:19.417
THERE'S CHUNKS.

53:23.458 --> 53:25.500
HI.

53:25.583 --> 53:28.166
I-- I-- -I'VE BEEN WONDERING
WHERE YOU'VE BEEN.

53:28.250 --> 53:31.333
WE HAVE TO TALK ABOUT STRIKER.

53:31.417 --> 53:35.750
NO, NO. YOU WILL STOP
AT NOTHING, WILL YOU?

53:37.500 --> 53:40.959
ALLISON. ALLISON.

53:41.917 --> 53:44.834
[ Moaning ]

53:46.458 --> 53:50.041
STRIKER?
ALLISON!

53:50.125 --> 53:51.083
MAGGIE.

53:52.125 --> 53:54.834
ALLISON, I'M-- I'M SO SORRY.

53:56.458 --> 53:59.458
YOU CAN ALL JUST GO TO HELL.

54:07.458 --> 54:10.166
[ Instrumental Music ]

54:15.333 --> 54:17.083
HEY, YOU.

54:17.166 --> 54:20.417
[ Sighs ]
SORRY ABOUT THIS
WHOLE PARTY THING.

54:20.500 --> 54:22.750
MY BROTHER IS
KIND OF AN ASSHOLE.

54:22.834 --> 54:24.458
KIND OF?

54:24.542 --> 54:26.250
I'M SERIOUSLY CONSIDERING
TELLING MOM

54:26.333 --> 54:28.000
WHERE HE KEEPS HIS PORN.

54:30.542 --> 54:32.500
THAT WAS A JOKE.

54:35.500 --> 54:38.250
KELLY, WHY DO YOU
HANG OUT WITH ME?

54:38.333 --> 54:40.375
I MEAN, YOU PROBABLY HAVE
BETTER THINGS TO DO

54:40.458 --> 54:45.041
THAN TO, UH, WASTE YOUR TIME
WITH A HAPLESS LOSER.

54:45.125 --> 54:49.417
YOU'RE NOT A LOSER, BERKE.
ALLISON THINKS SO.

54:49.500 --> 54:52.166
[ Whispers ]
ALLISON'S AN IDIOT.

54:53.166 --> 54:54.917
I HAVE DONE...

54:55.041 --> 54:59.083
ABSOLUTELY EVERYTHING
FOR THAT GIRL.

55:00.208 --> 55:02.333
SHE JUST DOESN'T GET IT.

55:09.208 --> 55:11.583
[ Guitar Music]

55:21.542 --> 55:24.000
[ Bird Calling ]

55:38.583 --> 55:40.250
I CAN'T DO THIS.

55:45.625 --> 55:48.583
KELLY, I THINK YOU'RE GREAT,
BUT WE CAN'T-- WE CAN'T DO THIS.

55:50.417 --> 55:52.417
YOU'RE FELIX'S LITTLE SISTER.

55:56.917 --> 55:58.375
SCREW YOU.

55:58.458 --> 56:01.709
KELLY, WAIT A SECOND.
THAT CAME OUT WRONG!

56:04.542 --> 56:07.834
WHAT WAS THAT?
FELIX, IT'S NOT WHAT YOU THINK.

56:09.542 --> 56:12.500
WHAT THE HELL
HAS GOTTEN INTO YOU?
AAH.

56:15.583 --> 56:20.500
WELL, WELL!
WHY AM I SUDDENLY GLAD WE
LEFT THE CONFERENCE EARLY?

56:20.583 --> 56:24.041
I DON'T RECALL ANYTHING
ABOUT A PARTY, BERKE.

56:24.125 --> 56:26.208
WE COULD HAVE SPRUNG
FOR A DEEJAY.

56:26.291 --> 56:29.208
MAKE SURE AND PUT THE FURNITURE
BACK WHEN YOU'RE DONE.

56:29.291 --> 56:33.583
MOM, DAD, REVEREND'S DAUGHTER,
JUDY, JUST TOOK A DUMP
IN OUR POOL

56:33.667 --> 56:35.375
AND YOU WANT TO SPRING
FOR A DEEJAY?

56:35.458 --> 56:38.083
THAT'S WHAT MAKES US SO FLY!

56:38.500 --> 56:40.250
WE TRUST YOU.

56:41.625 --> 56:44.959
YOU'RE MY PARENTS,
FOR GOD'S SAKES.
STOP TRUSTING ME!

56:50.792 --> 56:53.375
POOR JUDY.
I'LL GO GET THE SKIMMER.

57:07.709 --> 57:09.583
WELL, THIS IS
PRETTY INTERESTING.

57:09.667 --> 57:12.458
IT WAS NOTHING.
KELLY, I WAS THERE.

57:12.542 --> 57:15.917
HE KISSED YOU,
AND I DON'T KNOW WHY HE DID IT.

57:16.000 --> 57:17.792
I MEAN, BERKE'S PRETTY SCREWED
UP RIGHT NOW, BUT--

57:17.875 --> 57:20.500
LOOK, I KISSED HIM, TOO.

57:23.208 --> 57:28.417
AND, YES, HE IS SCREWED UP,
AND HE LIKES SOMEONE ELSE,
AND IT'S A PROBLEM,

57:28.500 --> 57:30.875
BUT, FELIX, IT'S MY PROBLEM.

57:37.458 --> 57:41.208
LOOK, YOU'D KNOW I'D BE LYING IF
I SAID I WAS HAPPY ABOUT THIS.

57:45.208 --> 57:50.166
BUT, UM, IF BERKE CAN'T SEE WHAT
AN AMAZING PERSON YOU ARE...

57:52.041 --> 57:54.917
THEN I'D SAY THAT HE'S THE ONE
WITH THE PROBLEM.

57:58.375 --> 57:59.542
GOOD NIGHT.

58:06.166 --> 58:09.083
[ Guitar Music ]

58:25.417 --> 58:27.166
[ On Tape ]
UH, HEY, IT'S-- IT'S ME.
IT'S BERKE.

58:27.250 --> 58:31.500
UH, JUST WANTED TO SAY THANKS
FOR ALL YOUR HELP.

58:31.583 --> 58:36.333
UH, THE GUY AT THE MUSIC STORE
SAID THAT SONGWRITERS USE
THESE THINGS, SO, UH--

58:36.417 --> 58:41.208
IF ANYONE CAN FIX
FORREST OATES' SONG,
IT'S-- IT'S DEFINITELY YOU.

58:41.291 --> 58:45.208
JUST KNOW THAT I-- I
BELIEVE IN YOU, KELLY.

58:45.291 --> 58:47.000
UM... BREAK A LEG.

58:47.083 --> 58:50.709
[ Man]
♪ NOW I'VE FALLEN IN DEEP ♪

58:50.792 --> 58:53.500
♪ SLOW, SILENT SLEEP ♪

58:53.583 --> 58:56.333
♪ IT'S KILLING ME ♪

58:56.417 --> 59:01.083
♪ I'M DYING ♪

59:19.792 --> 59:22.458
[ Instrumental Music ]

59:30.834 --> 59:34.667
HEY, LET'S MESS WITH
THE MORTALS ONE MORE TIME.
[ Giggling ]

59:34.750 --> 59:37.000
BOYFRIEND'LL BE
TRIPPIN' ON THIS.

59:38.000 --> 59:40.583
ONE MORE DOSE FOR MR. MOROSE.

59:40.667 --> 59:43.208
IT'S TIME FOR A LITTLE
WAKE-UP CALL.

59:43.291 --> 59:45.500
AND I'M OUTTA HERE.

59:49.291 --> 59:53.083
AND IN THE WOODS,
WHERE THE SCENTS ARE SWEET,

59:53.166 --> 59:56.375
THERE MY LYSANDER AND MYSELF
SHALL MEET.

01:00:06.291 --> 01:00:09.208
MAYBE IT'S TIME YOU STARTED
DREAMING OF SOMEONE ELSE.

01:00:09.291 --> 01:00:12.709
BERKE.
YOU WERE MY FIRST.

01:00:12.792 --> 01:00:14.583
NO ONE'S EVER
GONNA REPLACE YOU.

01:00:14.667 --> 01:00:18.250
I'VE DAZZLED MY WAY INTO
YOUR EX-GIRLFRIEND'S FANCIES.

01:00:18.333 --> 01:00:20.959
YOU WERE THE QUINTESSENTIAL
HIGH-SCHOOL COUPLE.

01:00:21.041 --> 01:00:24.959
SHE'S NOT YOUR GIRLFRIEND
ANYMORE, MAN.

01:00:25.041 --> 01:00:30.000
I'M MOVING ON WITH MY LIFE,
AND YOU'RE MOVING ON WITH YOURS.

01:00:30.083 --> 01:00:31.917
ARE WE FREAKING YOU OUT?
YEAH, WE'RE FREAKING HIM OUT.

01:00:32.000 --> 01:00:34.625
[ Jumbled Voices Speaking At
Once ]

01:00:34.709 --> 01:00:37.333
[ Screams ]

01:00:43.709 --> 01:00:46.667
UH, DR. FORREST OATES,
THE ATTENDANTS' COSTUMES
JUST ARRIVED.

01:00:46.750 --> 01:00:48.125
THANK BUDDHA.

01:00:48.208 --> 01:00:50.250
AND, UH, YOUR WIFE CALLED.

01:00:50.333 --> 01:00:53.291
SHE MIGHT NOT MAKE IT
TO TONIGHT'S PERFORMANCE.

01:00:53.375 --> 01:00:54.750
DID SHE SAY WHY?

01:00:54.834 --> 01:00:57.250
IT WAS DIFFICULT TO UNDERSTAND
THROUGH THE SLUR.

01:00:59.834 --> 01:01:02.792
UH, AND, SIR?
THERE IS ONE MORE THING.

01:01:02.875 --> 01:01:05.792
DEL MOLDEN, JR. IS SICK.

01:01:05.875 --> 01:01:09.125
MY DANCE PARTNER?

01:01:09.208 --> 01:01:11.834
THAT'S ENOUGH OUT OF YOU,
MCMOUTH!

01:01:11.917 --> 01:01:15.166
NOW, APPARENTLY, HE GOT HOLD
OF SOME TAINTED FRUIT PUNCH
LAST NIGHT...

01:01:15.250 --> 01:01:16.792
AND WON'T BE ABLE TO PERFORM.

01:01:16.875 --> 01:01:18.500
NOT THAT IT MATTERS AT ALL,

01:01:18.583 --> 01:01:21.667
BECAUSE THE ENTIRE PRODUCTION'S
GOING DOWN IN FLAMES, SO--

01:01:21.750 --> 01:01:24.500
[ Chuckling ]
OH.

01:01:24.583 --> 01:01:26.166
THAT HAVING BEEN SAID,

01:01:26.250 --> 01:01:28.166
I'M CURIOUS IF ANYONE
FEELS THAT THEY CAN FILL

01:01:28.250 --> 01:01:30.875
THE LITTLE BOOZE HOUND'S PLACE.

01:01:32.750 --> 01:01:34.500
GOOD. LET ME ASK YOU THIS.

01:01:34.583 --> 01:01:38.208
IS THERE ANYONE WHO, AT ALL,
IS GOOD ON THEIR FEET?

01:01:38.291 --> 01:01:42.834
A SHUFFLE, OR A TURN,
OR AN ATTITUDE OF ANY KIND

01:01:42.917 --> 01:01:44.166
WITH A POSE?

01:01:44.250 --> 01:01:45.667
WELL, UH--
[ Clears Throat ]

01:01:45.750 --> 01:01:47.333
SOMETIMES, UH, COACH HIBBLE

01:01:47.417 --> 01:01:48.792
CALLS ME CRAZY LEGS.

01:01:48.875 --> 01:01:50.417
OH, DOES HE?

01:01:51.875 --> 01:01:54.458
[ Instrumental Music ]

01:01:55.125 --> 01:01:56.709
WAIT. WAIT A SECOND.

01:01:56.792 --> 01:01:58.709
ALL RIGHT, MAYBE IF YOU
TOOK A HALF STEP BACK

01:01:58.792 --> 01:02:00.750
BEFORE THE SPIN.

01:02:00.834 --> 01:02:03.417
OK, JUST FOLLOW MY LEAD.

01:02:03.500 --> 01:02:05.792
I LEARNT THIS FROM
WATCHING IN THE WINGS.

01:02:07.166 --> 01:02:08.542
WOW!

01:02:08.625 --> 01:02:09.875
FELIX!

01:02:09.959 --> 01:02:11.667
KELLY, SHOULDN'T YOU
BE GETTING READY?

01:02:11.750 --> 01:02:13.917
I AM. I'M IN MAKEUP.

01:02:14.000 --> 01:02:16.667
LISTEN, I NEED YOU
TO DO A FAVOR FOR ME.

01:02:21.917 --> 01:02:24.375
[ Man ]
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
PLEASE TAKE YOUR SEATS.

01:02:24.458 --> 01:02:27.166
THE PERFORMANCE
IS ABOUT TO BEGIN.

01:02:27.917 --> 01:02:29.875
IT'S OVER.

01:02:29.959 --> 01:02:32.500
AFTER THIS ONE,
I'LL BE DIRECTING
ON THE STREETS.

01:02:34.166 --> 01:02:38.083
♪ ALL THE DOO-DAH NIGHT
ALL THE DOO-DAH DAY ♪

01:02:38.166 --> 01:02:40.083
♪ BET MY MONEY
ON A BOBTAIL NAG ♪

01:02:40.166 --> 01:02:42.834
♪ SOMEBODY BET ON THE BAY ♪
OHH!

01:02:46.208 --> 01:02:47.375
HEY.

01:02:48.458 --> 01:02:49.959
BREAK A LEG.

01:02:50.041 --> 01:02:52.750
[ Instruments Tuning Up ]

01:02:52.834 --> 01:02:54.125
GO-- GO AHEAD, JESSICA.

01:02:54.208 --> 01:02:55.583
RAISE THE CURTAIN
ON THE TRAGEDY

01:02:55.667 --> 01:02:57.959
THAT HAS BEFALLEN
THE BARD'S GREATEST COMEDY.

01:02:58.041 --> 01:03:00.750
I'M PRAYING FOR YOU, SIR.
THANKS.

01:03:00.834 --> 01:03:03.208
♪ [ Orchestra ]

01:03:09.875 --> 01:03:12.917
♪ DID YA EVER READ
A SHAKESPEARE PLAY ♪

01:03:13.000 --> 01:03:17.750
♪ OOH-OOH ♪
♪ AND NEVER UNDERSTAND
A WORD THEY SAY? ♪

01:03:17.834 --> 01:03:22.291
♪ AHH-AHH ♪
♪ WELL, TONIGHT WE'RE GONNA
MAKE THINGS CLEAR ♪

01:03:22.375 --> 01:03:24.625
♪ 'CAUSE SHAKESPEARE'S DEAD ♪

01:03:24.709 --> 01:03:27.750
♪ BUT WE'RE ALL HERE ♪

01:03:27.834 --> 01:03:30.291
[ Hooting, Cheering ]

01:03:30.375 --> 01:03:33.083
♪ WILLIAM SHAKESPEARE
WROTE A PLAY ♪

01:03:33.166 --> 01:03:35.959
♪ A LONG, LONG TIME AGO ♪

01:03:36.041 --> 01:03:38.417
♪ ABOUT THIS CHICK
NAMED HERMIA ♪

01:03:38.500 --> 01:03:40.959
♪ AND THE TWO GUYS
WHO LOVED HER SO ♪
♪ WHOA-OH ♪

01:03:41.041 --> 01:03:44.083
♪ THEY SAID, HERMIA,
PLEASE BE MY GIRL ♪

01:03:44.166 --> 01:03:46.917
♪ BUT SHE ONLY WANTED ONE ♪
♪ SHE WANTED ONE ♪

01:03:47.000 --> 01:03:49.625
♪ AND THE NIGHT
THE FAIRIES CAME TO PLAY ♪

01:03:49.709 --> 01:03:52.458
♪ THAT'S THE NIGHT
WE HAVE OUR FUN ♪

01:03:52.542 --> 01:03:55.417
♪ 'CAUSE I LOVE HIM ♪
♪ AND I LOVE HER ♪

01:03:55.500 --> 01:03:58.333
♪ IF ONLY HER BEST FRIEND
HE'D PREFER ♪

01:03:58.417 --> 01:04:01.041
♪ AND SO THE FAIRIES
ALL HATCHED A SCHEME ♪

01:04:01.125 --> 01:04:03.208
♪ IN THIS
BOOM-SHACKA-LACKA-LACKA ♪

01:04:03.291 --> 01:04:06.208
♪ MIDSUMMER NIGHT'S DREAM ♪

01:04:06.291 --> 01:04:08.959
♪ MIDSUMMER NIGHT'S DREAM ♪

01:04:09.041 --> 01:04:15.583
♪ MIDSUMMER NIGHT'S DREAM ♪

01:04:17.375 --> 01:04:18.750
[ Gasps ]

01:04:25.917 --> 01:04:28.542
LOOK, THERE'S HELENA.

01:04:28.625 --> 01:04:30.375
OH, FAIR HELENA.

01:04:30.458 --> 01:04:34.333
CALL YOU ME FAIR?
THAT FAIR AGAIN UNSAY.

01:04:34.417 --> 01:04:37.041
DOESN'T KELLY LOOK BEAUTIFUL?
MMM.

01:04:37.125 --> 01:04:40.250
DEMETRIUS AND LYSANDER
LOVE YOUR FAIR, HERMIA.

01:04:41.667 --> 01:04:44.875
OH, HAPPY FAIR.
[ Applauding ]

01:04:44.959 --> 01:04:47.250
♪ [ Disco Beat ]

01:04:47.333 --> 01:04:51.166
♪ OOH-OOH-OOH-OOH ♪
DO IT.

01:04:51.250 --> 01:04:52.875
YEAH, BABY.
DO IT.

01:04:52.959 --> 01:04:58.709
♪ OOH-OOH-OOH-OOH
OOH-OOH-WAAH-OHH ♪

01:04:58.792 --> 01:05:02.083
♪ IT'S FUN TO BE A FAIRY
AND FLY FROM TOWN TO TOWN ♪

01:05:02.166 --> 01:05:05.709
♪ OUR FAIRY DUST
WILL KEEP YOU UP
YOU WON'T COME DOWN ♪

01:05:05.792 --> 01:05:09.417
♪ YEAH, IT'S FUN TO BE A FAIRY
AND WEAR SUCH PRETTY THINGS ♪

01:05:09.500 --> 01:05:13.583
♪ IT'S FUN TO CARRY LOVE JUICE
ON YOUR FAIRY WINGS, YEAH ♪

01:05:13.667 --> 01:05:16.375
♪ WHAT FOOLS THESE MORTALS BE ♪

01:05:16.458 --> 01:05:21.083
♪ THAT TRY TO PLAY AT LOVE
AND MAKE A COMEDY, YEAH ♪

01:05:21.166 --> 01:05:23.917
♪ WHY CAN'T
THESE MORTALS LEARN ♪

01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:27.125
♪ A FAIRY UP ABOVE
WILL NEVER CRASH AND BURN ♪

01:05:27.208 --> 01:05:29.417
♪ YEAH, IT'S FUN
TO BE A FAIRY ♪
♪ THAT'S RIGHT ♪

01:05:29.500 --> 01:05:32.125
♪ OOH-OOH-OOH, YEAH
IT'S FUN TO BE A FAIRY ♪

01:05:32.208 --> 01:05:34.458
♪ THAT'S RIGHT ♪
♪ OOH-OOH-OOH, YEAH ♪

01:05:34.542 --> 01:05:38.125
♪ IT'S FUN TO BE A FAIRY
UH-HUH, UH-HUH, I LIKE IT ♪

01:05:38.208 --> 01:05:41.583
♪ IT'S FUN TO BE A FAIRY ♪
♪ GIVE IT UP, GIVE IT UP
GIVE IT UP, GIVE IT UP ♪

01:05:41.667 --> 01:05:45.917
♪ IT'S FUN TO BE A FAIRY ♪
IT'S FAIRY POWER!

01:05:46.000 --> 01:05:48.375
[ Cheering ]

01:05:52.959 --> 01:05:55.959
THAT WAS, UH--
THAT WAS OK!

01:05:57.166 --> 01:06:00.417
RELENT...
SWEET HERMIA.

01:06:00.500 --> 01:06:03.291
AND, LYSANDER,
YIELD THY CRAZED TITLE

01:06:03.375 --> 01:06:06.000
TO MY CERTAIN RIGHT.

01:06:06.083 --> 01:06:08.834
YOU HAVE HER FATHER'S LOVE,
DEMETRIUS.

01:06:08.917 --> 01:06:11.166
LET ME HAVE HERMIA'S.

01:06:12.041 --> 01:06:14.667
DO YOU MARRY HIM?

01:06:15.500 --> 01:06:18.625
SHIT, BUTT-WANKER. DICK-WEED.

01:06:18.709 --> 01:06:21.917
IT'S SO REAL,
YOU CAN ALMOST FEEL THE TENSION.

01:06:22.000 --> 01:06:23.083
WORD.

01:06:23.166 --> 01:06:28.166
♪ WHOO-OOH-OOH
WHY WON'T YOU LOVE ME? ♪

01:06:28.250 --> 01:06:32.458
♪ WHOO-OOH-OOH
WHOO-OOH-OOH-OOH ♪

01:06:32.542 --> 01:06:36.583
♪ THERE'S A GIRL ♪
♪ WHO SAYS SHE DON'T LOVE ME ♪

01:06:36.667 --> 01:06:40.750
♪ SO THAT'S THE GIRL ♪
♪ THAT I GOT TO HAVE ♪

01:06:40.834 --> 01:06:45.542
♪ I'LL TELL YOU WHY ♪
♪ SHE'S EVERYTHING
A GIRL OUGHT TO BE ♪

01:06:45.625 --> 01:06:48.625
♪ AND THAT IS WHY ♪
♪ I CAN'T UNDERSTAND ♪

01:06:48.709 --> 01:06:51.667
♪ WHY SHE DON'T LOVE ME ♪
NO ♪

01:06:51.750 --> 01:06:53.458
♪ HERMIA ♪

01:06:53.542 --> 01:06:56.000
♪ I'LL MAKE YOU LOVE ME ♪

01:06:56.083 --> 01:06:58.166
♪ HERMIA ♪

01:06:58.250 --> 01:07:01.000
♪ I'LL MAKE YOU CARE ♪

01:07:01.083 --> 01:07:04.000
♪ NEVER BEFORE HAS A GIRL ♪

01:07:04.083 --> 01:07:05.166
♪ HURT ME MORE ♪

01:07:05.250 --> 01:07:09.166
♪ I'M BEGGING HERMIA ♪

01:07:09.250 --> 01:07:12.000
♪ PLEASE LOVE ME ♪

01:07:12.083 --> 01:07:13.041
BITCH.
PANZY.

01:07:13.125 --> 01:07:14.166
♪ WHY WON'T YOU LOVE ME? ♪

01:07:14.250 --> 01:07:16.125
♪ PLEASE LOVE ME ♪

01:07:16.208 --> 01:07:18.083
ASSHOLE.

01:07:30.625 --> 01:07:32.041
HMM, HMM.

01:07:32.125 --> 01:07:36.208
I'LL APPLY TO YOUR EYE
GENTLE LOVER'S REMEDY.

01:07:36.291 --> 01:07:38.250
AND WHEN THOU WAKEST,

01:07:38.333 --> 01:07:40.500
THOU WILL TAKEST
TRUE DELIGHT...

01:07:40.583 --> 01:07:43.250
IN THE SIGHT
OF THY TRUE LOVER'S EYE.

01:07:49.083 --> 01:07:51.834
OK, PEOPLE, WE'RE BACK IN 20.

01:07:51.917 --> 01:07:55.041
BERKE, BERKE, I, UM,
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT SOMETHING.

01:07:55.125 --> 01:07:57.208
CAN WE GO SOMEWHERE?
YEAH.

01:07:57.291 --> 01:07:58.667
THANK YOU.

01:08:03.750 --> 01:08:04.917
WELL.

01:08:06.333 --> 01:08:09.250
[ Sighs ]
I COULD USE A DRINK.
YEAH.

01:08:09.333 --> 01:08:11.709
KAISHA, YOU'RE JUST NOT EQUIPPED
TO DEAL WITH THIS.
I'M TALKING EQUIPMENT.

01:08:11.792 --> 01:08:14.917
OH, HARDWARE.
WE'RE TALKING 800 NUMBER.
SHE WANTS A BLOW-UP DOLL, RIGHT?

01:08:15.000 --> 01:08:17.291
I CALLED THEM ONCE FOR ADVICE.

01:08:17.375 --> 01:08:19.250
REALLY?

01:08:19.332 --> 01:08:22.166
YEAH. I HAD ZITS ON MY BALLS.

01:08:23.332 --> 01:08:25.291
THEY'RE GONE NOW.

01:08:27.166 --> 01:08:30.082
GENTLEMEN,
I'M HERE FOR A FAVOR.

01:08:30.166 --> 01:08:32.250
IN ACT FOUR, SCENE ONE,

01:08:32.332 --> 01:08:35.250
THERE'S A PARTICULAR
EFFECTS CUE.

01:08:35.332 --> 01:08:38.917
AH, THE VOLK TUBE CRESCENDO.

01:08:39.000 --> 01:08:40.457
RIGHT. NOW, IS THIS THE ONE?

01:08:40.542 --> 01:08:44.792
UH, NO. THAT ONE
COULD TAKE OUT A VILLAGE.

01:08:44.875 --> 01:08:47.417
HMM. I SEE.

01:08:47.500 --> 01:08:50.125
WELL, I WAS WONDERING
IF YOU MIGHT BE ABLE

01:08:50.207 --> 01:08:53.500
TO DETONATE IT A BIT...
EARLY.

01:08:53.582 --> 01:08:56.332
ISN'T THAT BEFORE
MR. LANDER'S CROSS?

01:08:56.417 --> 01:08:58.250
LOOK, ALL IT'LL DO
IS SCARE HIM.

01:08:58.332 --> 01:09:00.834
I CAN SIGNAL YOU
BY RAISING MY SWORD LIKE THIS.

01:09:03.207 --> 01:09:07.291
LOOK, ABOUT THIS WHOLE THING
WITH STRIKER,
I'M SORRY I DIDN'T BELIEVE YOU.

01:09:07.375 --> 01:09:11.959
I'M SORRY YOU HAD TO FIND OUT
LIKE THAT. IT KINDA SUCKED.

01:09:12.041 --> 01:09:16.500
LOOK, I-- I KNOW I DON'T DESERVE
TO ASK YOU ANYTHING
RIGHT NOW, BUT...

01:09:16.582 --> 01:09:19.457
IF I COULD JUST HAVE ONE WISH,

01:09:19.542 --> 01:09:24.250
IT WOULD BE THAT WE COULD
GO BACK TO THE WAY THINGS WERE.

01:09:24.332 --> 01:09:25.667
YOU KNOW?

01:09:25.750 --> 01:09:29.959
I-- I MEAN, THE FRIENDS PART.
YEAH, SURE.

01:09:31.457 --> 01:09:34.082
AND AS FOR THE REST OF IT,
WELL...

01:09:41.709 --> 01:09:44.250
WE'LL JUST LEAVE IT UP TO FATE.

01:09:46.082 --> 01:09:48.457
[ Instrumental Music ]

01:09:51.041 --> 01:09:55.625
DID I MENTION THERE WAS
$47 IN IT FOR YOU?

01:09:56.375 --> 01:09:58.166
NOT BAD.

01:09:58.250 --> 01:10:02.959
HMM, I BELIEVE,
MR. SCRUMFELD,

01:10:03.041 --> 01:10:04.291
WE HAVE AN UNDERSTANDING.

01:10:04.375 --> 01:10:09.041
REMEMBER, GENTLEMEN,
WHEN I RAISE MY SWORD.

01:10:13.834 --> 01:10:16.834
HEY, UH, THE-- THE MUSIC'S
BEEN, UH, BEEN-- BEEN GOOD,

01:10:16.917 --> 01:10:20.709
BUT, UH, YOU KNOW THAT SONG, UH,
"A POCKETFUL OF, UH, DREAMS?"

01:10:20.792 --> 01:10:23.250
DOWN HERE WE CALL IT
"POCKETFUL OF ASS."
YEAH, THAT'S THE ONE.

01:10:23.333 --> 01:10:25.542
LISTEN, THERE'S BEEN
A CHANGE OF PLANS.

01:10:25.625 --> 01:10:28.291
[ Bells Chiming ]

01:10:29.125 --> 01:10:31.208
OH, THIS IS DIFFERENT.

01:10:31.291 --> 01:10:33.667
♪ [ Orchestra ]

01:10:39.500 --> 01:10:42.041
A SPELL HAD BEEN CAST,

01:10:42.125 --> 01:10:44.375
THE LOVERS SLEEP,

01:10:44.458 --> 01:10:46.375
THOUGH IN REPOSE,

01:10:46.458 --> 01:10:50.291
FAIR HELENA'S LOVE
FOR DEMETRIUS GROWS.

01:10:51.458 --> 01:10:53.917
♪ [ Piano Music ]

01:10:55.000 --> 01:10:57.875
O WEARY NIGHT,

01:10:57.959 --> 01:10:59.333
ABATE THY HOURS.

01:11:01.500 --> 01:11:04.375
STEAL ME AWHILE
FROM MY OWN COMPANY.

01:11:11.166 --> 01:11:15.250
♪ LET ME SLEEP ♪

01:11:15.333 --> 01:11:18.750
♪ FOR WHEN I SLEEP I DREAM ♪

01:11:18.834 --> 01:11:22.291
♪ THAT YOU ARE HERE ♪

01:11:22.375 --> 01:11:25.208
♪ YOU'RE MINE ♪

01:11:25.291 --> 01:11:27.458
♪ AND ALL MY FEARS ♪

01:11:27.542 --> 01:11:30.083
♪ ARE LEFT BEHIND ♪

01:11:30.166 --> 01:11:32.417
♪ I FLOAT ♪

01:11:32.500 --> 01:11:34.625
♪ ON AIR ♪

01:11:34.709 --> 01:11:37.750
♪ THE NIGHTINGALE SINGS ♪

01:11:37.834 --> 01:11:42.291
♪ GENTLE LULLABIES ♪

01:11:42.375 --> 01:11:47.458
♪ SO LET ME CLOSE MY EYES ♪

01:11:47.542 --> 01:11:49.500
JESSICA! JESSICA!

01:11:49.583 --> 01:11:54.417
♪ AND SLEEP
PERCHANCE TO DREAM ♪

01:11:54.500 --> 01:11:58.125
♪ SO I CAN SEE THE FACE ♪

01:11:58.208 --> 01:12:01.959
♪ I LONG TO TOUCH ♪

01:12:02.041 --> 01:12:04.291
♪ TO KISS ♪

01:12:04.375 --> 01:12:06.458
♪ BUT ONLY DREAMS ♪

01:12:06.542 --> 01:12:08.625
♪ CAN BRING ME THIS ♪

01:12:08.709 --> 01:12:13.625
♪ SO LET THE MOON ♪

01:12:13.709 --> 01:12:17.291
♪ SHINE SOFTLY ON THE BOY ♪

01:12:17.375 --> 01:12:21.333
♪ I LONG TO SEE ♪

01:12:21.417 --> 01:12:26.500
♪ AND MAYBE WHEN HE DREAMS ♪

01:12:26.583 --> 01:12:31.583
♪ HE'LL DREAM OF ME ♪

01:12:38.792 --> 01:12:43.500
♪ HIDE BENEATH THE CLOUDS ♪

01:12:43.583 --> 01:12:48.500
♪ AND WHISPER
TO THE EVENING STAR ♪

01:12:48.583 --> 01:12:50.500
♪ THEY TELL ME LOVE ♪

01:12:50.583 --> 01:12:55.500
♪ IS JUST A DREAM AWAY ♪

01:12:55.583 --> 01:12:59.542
♪ DREAM AWAY ♪

01:12:59.625 --> 01:13:04.166
♪ I'LL DREAM AWAY ♪

01:13:04.250 --> 01:13:05.625
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

01:13:19.750 --> 01:13:24.667
♪ SO LET THE MOON ♪

01:13:24.750 --> 01:13:28.500
♪ SHINE SOFTLY ON THE BOY ♪

01:13:28.583 --> 01:13:32.583
♪ I LONG TO SEE ♪

01:13:32.667 --> 01:13:37.583
♪ AND MAYBE WHEN HE DREAMS ♪

01:13:37.667 --> 01:13:42.875
♪ HE'LL DREAM OF ME ♪

01:13:46.500 --> 01:13:49.125
♪ OH-OH-OH-OH ♪

01:13:49.208 --> 01:13:54.667
♪ DREAM OF ME ♪

01:13:58.291 --> 01:13:59.667
[ Man ]
WHOO!

01:14:15.500 --> 01:14:19.667
GO BID THE HUNTSMEN. WAKE THEM
WITH-- WITH THEIR HORNS.

01:14:20.667 --> 01:14:23.709
♪ [ Horn: Fanfare ]

01:14:25.709 --> 01:14:27.625
MY LORD,
I SHALL REPLY AMAZEDLY,

01:14:27.709 --> 01:14:30.458
HALF SLEEP, HALF WAKING.

